  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: bd3f8ba6a2445b646991a3e44f7f687a, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Now king David was old <i>and</i> stricken in years; and they covered
        him with clothes, but he gat no heat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Wherefore his servants said unto him, Let there be sought for my
        lord the king a young virgin: and let her stand before the king, and let
        her cherish him, and let her lie in thy bosom, that my lord the king may
        get heat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they sought for a fair damsel throughout all the coasts of Israel,
        and found Abishag a Shunammite, and brought her to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: David''s Successor'
      title: David's Successor
      number: 4
      content: 'And the damsel <i>was</i> very fair, and cherished the king, and
        ministered to him: but the king knew her not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, I will
        be king: and he prepared him chariots and horsemen, and fifty men to run
        before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And his father had not displeased him at any time in saying, Why
        hast thou done so? and he also <i>was</i> a very goodly man; and <i>his mother</i>
        bare him after Absalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah, and with Abiathar
        the priest: and they following Adonijah helped <i>him</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and Nathan
        the prophet, and Shimei, and Rei, and the mighty men which <i>belonged</i>
        to David, were not with Adonijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Adonijah slew sheep and oxen and fat cattle by the stone of Zoheleth,
        which <i>is</i> by En-rogel, and called all his brethren the king''s sons,
        and all the men of Judah the king''s servants: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah, and the mighty men, and Solomon
        his brother, he called not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wherefore Nathan spake unto Bath-sheba the mother of Solomon, saying,
        Hast thou not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith doth reign, and David
        our lord knoweth <i>it</i> not? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now therefore come, let me, I pray thee, give thee counsel, that
        thou mayest save thine own life, and the life of thy son Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Go and get thee in unto king David, and say unto him, Didst not thou,
        my lord, O king, swear unto thine handmaid, saying, Assuredly Solomon thy
        son shall reign after me, and he shall sit upon my throne? why then doth
        Adonijah reign? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Behold, while thou yet talkest there with the king, I also will come
        in after thee, and confirm thy words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Bath-sheba went in unto the king into the chamber: and the king
        was very old; and Abishag the Shunammite ministered unto the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Bath-sheba bowed, and did obeisance unto the king. And the king
        said, What wouldest thou? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And she said unto him, My lord, thou swarest by the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        thy God unto thine handmaid, <i>saying</i>, Assuredly Solomon thy son shall
        reign after me, and he shall sit upon my throne. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And now, behold, Adonijah reigneth; and now, my lord the king, thou
        knowest <i>it</i> not: '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and he hath slain oxen and fat cattle and sheep in abundance, and
        hath called all the sons of the king, and Abiathar the priest, and Joab the
        captain of the host: but Solomon thy servant hath he not called. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And thou, my lord, O king, the eyes of all Israel <i>are</i> upon
        thee, that thou shouldest tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord
        the king after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Otherwise it shall come to pass, when my lord the king shall sleep
        with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon shall be counted offenders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And, lo, while she yet talked with the king, Nathan the prophet also
        came in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they told the king, saying, Behold Nathan the prophet. And when
        he was come in before the king, he bowed himself before the king with his
        face to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Nathan said, My lord, O king, hast thou said, Adonijah shall
        reign after me, and he shall sit upon my throne? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For he is gone down this day, and hath slain oxen and fat cattle
        and sheep in abundance, and hath called all the king''s sons, and the captains
        of the host, and Abiathar the priest; and, behold, they eat and drink before
        him, and say, God save king Adonijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But me, <i>even</i> me thy servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah
        the son of Jehoiada, and thy servant Solomon, hath he not called. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Is this thing done by my lord the king, and thou hast not shewed
        <i>it</i> unto thy servant, who should sit on the throne of my lord the king
        after him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then king David answered and said, Call me Bath-sheba. And she came
        into the king''s presence, and stood before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the king sware, and said, <i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        liveth, that hath redeemed my soul out of all distress, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'even as I sware unto thee by the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel, saying, Assuredly Solomon thy son shall reign after me, and he
        shall sit upon my throne in my stead; even so will I certainly do this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Bath-sheba bowed with <i>her</i> face to the earth, and did
        reverence to the king, and said, Let my lord king David live for ever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And king David said, Call me Zadok the priest, and Nathan the prophet,
        and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada. And they came before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The king also said unto them, Take with you the servants of your
        lord, and cause Solomon my son to ride upon mine own mule, and bring him
        down to Gihon: '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint him there
        king over Israel: and blow ye with the trumpet, and say, God save king Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then ye shall come up after him, that he may come and sit upon my
        throne; for he shall be king in my stead: and I have appointed him to be
        ruler over Israel and over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king, and said, Amen:
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of my lord the king say so <i>too</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'As the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath been with my lord the king,
        even so be he with Solomon, and make his throne greater than the throne of
        my lord king David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Zadok the priest, and Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son
        of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites, and the Pelethites, went down, and caused
        Solomon to ride upon king David''s mule, and brought him to Gihon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And Zadok the priest took an horn of oil out of the tabernacle, and
        anointed Solomon. And they blew the trumpet; and all the people said, God
        save king Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And all the people came up after him, and the people piped with pipes,
        and rejoiced with great joy, so that the earth rent with the sound of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Adonijah and all the guests that <i>were</i> with him heard <i>it</i>
        as they had made an end of eating. And when Joab heard the sound of the trumpet,
        he said, Wherefore <i>is this</i> noise of the city being in an uproar? '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And while he yet spake, behold, Jonathan the son of Abiathar the
        priest came: and Adonijah said unto him, Come in; for thou <i>art</i> a valiant
        man, and bringest good tidings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And Jonathan answered and said to Adonijah, Verily our lord king
        David hath made Solomon king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And the king hath sent with him Zadok the priest, and Nathan the
        prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites, and the Pelethites,
        and they have caused him to ride upon the king''s mule: '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'and Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king
        in Gihon: and they are come up from thence rejoicing, so that the city rang
        again. This <i>is</i> the noise that ye have heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And also Solomon sitteth on the throne of the kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And moreover the king''s servants came to bless our lord king David,
        saying, God make the name of Solomon better than thy name, and make his throne
        greater than thy throne. And the king bowed himself upon the bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And also thus said the king, Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel, which hath given <i>one</i> to sit on my throne this day,
        mine eyes even seeing <i>it</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And all the guests that <i>were</i> with Adonijah were afraid, and
        rose up, and went every man his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'And Adonijah feared because of Solomon, and arose, and went, and
        caught hold on the horns of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'And it was told Solomon, saying, Behold, Adonijah feareth king Solomon:
        for, lo, he hath caught hold on the horns of the altar, saying, Let king
        Solomon swear unto me to day that he will not slay his servant with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And Solomon said, If he will shew himself a worthy man, there shall
        not an hair of him fall to the earth: but if wickedness shall be found in
        him, he shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'So king Solomon sent, and they brought him down from the altar. And
        he came and bowed himself to king Solomon: and Solomon said unto him, Go
        to thine house.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David''s Charge to Solomon'
      title: David's Charge to Solomon
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the days of David drew nigh that he should die; and he charged
        Solomon his son, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I go the way of all the earth: be thou strong therefore, and shew
        thyself a man; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and keep the charge of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God, to
        walk in his ways, to keep his statutes, and his commandments, and his judgments,
        and his testimonies, as it is written in the law of Moses, that thou mayest
        prosper in all that thou doest, and whithersoever thou turnest thyself: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> may continue his word which
        he spake concerning me, saying, If thy children take heed to their way, to
        walk before me in truth with all their heart and with all their soul, there
        shall not fail thee (said he) a man on the throne of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Moreover thou knowest also what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to me,
        <i>and</i> what he did to the two captains of the hosts of Israel, unto Abner
        the son of Ner, and unto Amasa the son of Jether, whom he slew, and shed
        the blood of war in peace, and put the blood of war upon his girdle that
        <i>was</i> about his loins, and in his shoes that <i>were</i> on his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do therefore according to thy wisdom, and let not his hoar head go
        down to the grave in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But shew kindness unto the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let
        them be of those that eat at thy table: for so they came to me when I fled
        because of Absalom thy brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And, behold, <i>thou hast</i> with thee Shimei the son of Gera, a
        Benjamite of Bahurim, which cursed me with a grievous curse in the day when
        I went to Mahanaim: but he came down to meet me at Jordan, and I sware to
        him by the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, saying, I will not put thee to death
        with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now therefore hold him not guiltless: for thou <i>art</i> a wise
        man, and knowest what thou oughtest to do unto him; but his hoar head bring
        thou down to the grave with blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So David slept with his fathers, and was buried in the city of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the days that David reigned over Israel <i>were</i> forty years:
        seven years reigned he in Hebron, and thirty and three years reigned he in
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then sat Solomon upon the throne of David his father; and his kingdom
        was established greatly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bath-sheba the mother of
        Solomon. And she said, Comest thou peaceably? And he said, Peaceably. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He said moreover, I have somewhat to say unto thee. And she said,
        Say on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he said, Thou knowest that the kingdom was mine, and <i>that</i>
        all Israel set their faces on me, that I should reign: howbeit the kingdom
        is turned about, and is become my brother''s: for it was his from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And now I ask one petition of thee, deny me not. And she said unto
        him, Say on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he said, Speak, I pray thee, unto Solomon the king, (for he will
        not say thee nay,) that he give me Abishag the Shunammite to wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Bath-sheba said, Well; I will speak for thee unto the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Bath-sheba therefore went unto king Solomon, to speak unto him for
        Adonijah. And the king rose up to meet her, and bowed himself unto her, and
        sat down on his throne, and caused a seat to be set for the king''s mother;
        and she sat on his right hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then she said, I desire one small petition of thee; <i>I pray thee</i>,
        say me not nay. And the king said unto her, Ask on, my mother: for I will
        not say thee nay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And she said, Let Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah thy
        brother to wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And king Solomon answered and said unto his mother, And why dost
        thou ask Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? ask for him the kingdom also;
        for he <i>is</i> mine elder brother; even for him, and for Abiathar the priest,
        and for Joab the son of Zeruiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then king Solomon sware by the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, saying,
        God do so to me, and more also, if Adonijah have not spoken this word against
        his own life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now therefore, <i>as</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> liveth,
        which hath established me, and set me on the throne of David my father, and
        who hath made me an house, as he promised, Adonijah shall be put to death
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And king Solomon sent by the hand of Benaiah the son of Jehoiada;
        and he fell upon him that he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And unto Abiathar the priest said the king, Get thee to Anathoth,
        unto thine own fields; for thou <i>art</i> worthy of death: but I will not
        at this time put thee to death, because thou barest the ark of the Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>
        before David my father, and because thou hast been afflicted in all wherein
        my father was afflicted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Solomon thrust out Abiathar from being priest unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        that he might fulfil the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which he
        spake concerning the house of Eli in Shiloh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then tidings came to Joab: for Joab had turned after Adonijah, though
        he turned not after Absalom. And Joab fled unto the tabernacle of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and caught hold on the horns of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And it was told king Solomon that Joab was fled unto the tabernacle
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; and, behold, <i>he is</i> by the altar.
        Then Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, saying, Go, fall upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Benaiah came to the tabernacle of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and said unto him, Thus saith the king, Come forth. And he said, Nay; but
        I will die here. And Benaiah brought the king word again, saying, Thus said
        Joab, and thus he answered me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the king said unto him, Do as he hath said, and fall upon him,
        and bury him; that thou mayest take away the innocent blood, which Joab shed,
        from me, and from the house of my father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall return his blood upon his
        own head, who fell upon two men more righteous and better than he, and slew
        them with the sword, my father David not knowing <i>thereof, to wit</i>,
        Abner the son of Ner, captain of the host of Israel, and Amasa the son of
        Jether, captain of the host of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Their blood shall therefore return upon the head of Joab, and upon
        the head of his seed for ever: but upon David, and upon his seed, and upon
        his house, and upon his throne, shall there be peace for ever from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up, and fell upon him, and slew
        him: and he was buried in his own house in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the king put Benaiah the son of Jehoiada in his room over the
        host: and Zadok the priest did the king put in the room of Abiathar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And the king sent and called for Shimei, and said unto him, Build
        thee an house in Jerusalem, and dwell there, and go not forth thence any
        whither. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For it shall be, <i>that</i> on the day thou goest out, and passest
        over the brook Kidron, thou shalt know for certain that thou shalt surely
        die: thy blood shall be upon thine own head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And Shimei said unto the king, The saying <i>is</i> good: as my lord
        the king hath said, so will thy servant do. And Shimei dwelt in Jerusalem
        many days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And it came to pass at the end of three years, that two of the servants
        of Shimei ran away unto Achish son of Maachah king of Gath. And they told
        Shimei, saying, Behold, thy servants <i>be</i> in Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And Shimei arose, and saddled his ass, and went to Gath to Achish
        to seek his servants: and Shimei went, and brought his servants from Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And it was told Solomon that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath,
        and was come again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And the king sent and called for Shimei, and said unto him, Did I
        not make thee to swear by the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and protested
        unto thee, saying, Know for a certain, on the day thou goest out, and walkest
        abroad any whither, that thou shalt surely die? and thou saidst unto me,
        The word <i>that</i> I have heard <i>is</i> good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Why then hast thou not kept the oath of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and the commandment that I have charged thee with? '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The king said moreover to Shimei, Thou knowest all the wickedness
        which thine heart is privy to, that thou didst to David my father: therefore
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall return thy wickedness upon thine own
        head; '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'and king Solomon <i>shall be</i> blessed, and the throne of David
        shall be established before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: So the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; which went out,
        and fell upon him, that he died. And the kingdom was established in the hand
        of Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Marriage to Pharaoh''s Daughter'
      title: Marriage to Pharaoh's Daughter
      number: 1
      content: '  And Solomon made affinity with Pharaoh king of Egypt, and took
        Pharaoh''s daughter, and brought her into the city of David, until he had
        made an end of building his own house, and the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and the wall of Jerusalem round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Only the people sacrificed in high places, because there was no house
        built unto the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, until those days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Solomon loved the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, walking in the
        statutes of David his father: only he sacrificed and burnt incense in high
        places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Solomon''s Choice of Wisdom'
      title: Solomon's Choice of Wisdom
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king went to Gibeon to sacrifice there; for that <i>was</i>
        the great high place: a thousand burnt offerings did Solomon offer upon that
        altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In Gibeon the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> appeared to Solomon in
        a dream by night: and God said, Ask what I shall give thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Solomon said, Thou hast shewed unto thy servant David my father
        great mercy, according as he walked before thee in truth, and in righteousness,
        and in uprightness of heart with thee; and thou hast kept for him this great
        kindness, that thou hast given him a son to sit on his throne, as <i>it is</i>
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And now, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> my God, thou hast made thy
        servant king instead of David my father: and I <i>am but</i> a little child:
        I know not <i>how</i> to go out or come in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And thy servant <i>is</i> in the midst of thy people which thou hast
        chosen, a great people, that cannot be numbered nor counted for multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Give therefore thy servant an understanding heart to judge thy people,
        that I may discern between good and bad: for who is able to judge this thy
        so great a people?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the speech pleased the Lord, that Solomon had asked this thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And God said unto him, Because thou hast asked this thing, and hast
        not asked for thyself long life; neither hast asked riches for thyself, nor
        hast asked the life of thine enemies; but hast asked for thyself understanding
        to discern judgment; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'behold, I have done according to thy words: lo, I have given thee
        a wise and an understanding heart; so that there was none like thee before
        thee, neither after thee shall any arise like unto thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I have also given thee that which thou hast not asked, both riches,
        and honour: so that there shall not be any among the kings like unto thee
        all thy days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And if thou wilt walk in my ways, to keep my statutes and my commandments,
        as thy father David did walk, then I will lengthen thy days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Solomon awoke; and, behold, <i>it was</i> a dream. And he came
        to Jerusalem, and stood before the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and offered up burnt offerings, and offered peace offerings, and made a feast
        to all his servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then came there two women, <i>that were</i> harlots, unto the king,
        and stood before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the one woman said, O my lord, I and this woman dwell in one
        house; and I was delivered of a child with her in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And it came to pass the third day after that I was delivered, that
        this woman was delivered also: and we <i>were</i> together; <i>there was</i>
        no stranger with us in the house, save we two in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And this woman''s child died in the night; because she overlaid it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And she arose at midnight, and took my son from beside me, while
        thine handmaid slept, and laid it in her bosom, and laid her dead child in
        my bosom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when I rose in the morning to give my child suck, behold, it
        was dead: but when I had considered it in the morning, behold, it was not
        my son, which I did bear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the other woman said, Nay; but the living <i>is</i> my son, and
        the dead <i>is</i> thy son. And this said, No; but the dead <i>is</i> thy
        son, and the living <i>is</i> my son. Thus they spake before the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then said the king, The one saith, This <i>is</i> my son that liveth,
        and thy son <i>is</i> the dead: and the other saith, Nay; but thy son <i>is</i>
        the dead, and my son <i>is</i> the living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the king said, Bring me a sword. And they brought a sword before
        the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the king said, Divide the living child in two, and give half
        to the one, and half to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then spake the woman whose the living child <i>was</i> unto the king,
        for her bowels yearned upon her son, and she said, O my lord, give her the
        living child, and in no wise slay it. But the other said, Let it be neither
        mine nor thine, <i>but</i> divide <i>it</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the king answered and said, Give her the living child, and in
        no wise slay it: she <i>is</i> the mother thereof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And all Israel heard of the judgment which the king had judged; and
        they feared the king: for they saw that the wisdom of God <i>was</i> in him,
        to do judgment.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: His Princes'
      title: His Princes
      number: 1
      content: '  So king Solomon was king over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And these <i>were</i> the princes which he had; Azariah the son of
        Zadok the priest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elihoreph and Ahiah, the sons of Shisha, scribes; Jehoshaphat the
        son of Ahilud, the recorder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada <i>was</i> over the host: and Zadok
        and Abiathar <i>were</i> the priests: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Azariah the son of Nathan <i>was</i> over the officers: and Zabud
        the son of Nathan <i>was</i> principal officer, <i>and</i> the king''s friend: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Ahishar <i>was</i> over the household: and Adoniram the son of
        Abda <i>was</i> over the tribute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Solomon had twelve officers over all Israel, which provided victuals
        for the king and his household: each man his month in a year made provision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And these <i>are</i> their names: The son of Hur, in mount Ephraim: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the son of Dekar, in Makaz, and in Shaalbim, and Beth-shemesh, and
        Elon-beth-hanan: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the son of Hesed, in Aruboth; to him <i>pertained</i> Sochoh, and
        all the land of Hepher: '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the son of Abinadab, in all the region of Dor; which had Taphath
        the daughter of Solomon to wife: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Baana the son of Ahilud; <i>to him pertained</i> Taanach and Megiddo,
        and all Beth-shean, which <i>is</i> by Zartanah beneath Jezreel, from Beth-shean
        to Abel-meholah, <i>even</i> unto <i>the place that is</i> beyond Jokneam: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the son of Geber, in Ramoth-gilead; to him <i>pertained</i> the towns
        of Jair the son of Manasseh, which <i>are</i> in Gilead; to him <i>also pertained</i>
        the region of Argob, which <i>is</i> in Bashan, threescore great cities with
        walls and brasen bars: '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ahinadab the son of Iddo <i>had</i> Mahanaim: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ahimaaz <i>was</i> in Naphtali; he also took Basmath the daughter
        of Solomon to wife: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Baanah the son of Hushai <i>was</i> in Asher and in Aloth: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar: '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Shimei the son of Elah, in Benjamin: '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Geber the son of Uri <i>was</i> in the country of Gilead, <i>in</i>
        the country of Sihon king of the Amorites, and of Og king of Bashan; and
        <i>he was</i> the only officer which <i>was</i> in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Judah and Israel <i>were</i> many, as the sand which <i>is</i> by
        the sea in multitude, eating and drinking, and making merry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Solomon reigned over all kingdoms from the river unto the land
        of the Philistines, and unto the border of Egypt: they brought presents,
        and served Solomon all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Solomon''s provision for one day was thirty measures of fine
        flour, and threescore measures of meal, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'ten fat oxen, and twenty oxen out of the pastures, and an hundred
        sheep, beside harts, and roebucks, and fallow deer, and fatted fowl. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For he had dominion over all <i>the region</i> on this side the river,
        from Tiphsah even to Azzah, over all the kings on this side the river: and
        he had peace on all sides round about him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Judah and Israel dwelt safely, every man under his vine and under
        his fig tree, from Dan even to Beer-sheba, all the days of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Solomon had forty thousand stalls of horses for his chariots,
        and twelve thousand horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And those officers provided victual for king Solomon, and for all
        that came unto king Solomon''s table, every man in his month: they lacked
        nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Barley also and straw for the horses and dromedaries brought they
        unto the place where <i>the officers</i> were, every man according to his
        charge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And God gave Solomon wisdom and understanding exceeding much, and
        largeness of heart, even as the sand that <i>is</i> on the sea shore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Solomon''s wisdom excelled the wisdom of all the children of
        the east country, and all the wisdom of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For he was wiser than all men; than Ethan the Ezrahite, and Heman,
        and Chalcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol: and his fame was in all nations
        round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he spake three thousand proverbs: and his songs were a thousand
        and five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he spake of trees, from the cedar tree that <i>is</i> in Lebanon
        even unto the hyssop that springeth out of the wall: he spake also of beasts,
        and of fowl, and of creeping things, and of fishes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And there came of all people to hear the wisdom of Solomon, from all
        kings of the earth, which had heard of his wisdom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Building the Temple'
      title: Building the Temple
      number: 1
      content: '  And Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants unto Solomon; for he had
        heard that they had anointed him king in the room of his father: for Hiram
        was ever a lover of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Solomon sent to Hiram, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thou knowest how that David my father could not build an house unto
        the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God for the wars which were
        about him on every side, until the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> put them under
        the soles of his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But now the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> my God hath given me rest
        on every side, <i>so that there is</i> neither adversary nor evil occurrent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And, behold, I purpose to build an house unto the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        my God, as the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> spake unto David my father, saying,
        Thy son, whom I will set upon thy throne in thy room, he shall build an house
        unto my name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now therefore command thou that they hew me cedar trees out of Lebanon;
        and my servants shall be with thy servants: and unto thee will I give hire
        for thy servants according to all that thou shalt appoint: for thou knowest
        that <i>there is</i> not among us any that can skill to hew timber like unto
        the Sidonians.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Hiram heard the words of Solomon, that
        he rejoiced greatly, and said, Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        this day, which hath given unto David a wise son over this great people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Hiram sent to Solomon, saying, I have considered the things which
        thou sentest to me for: <i>and</i> I will do all thy desire concerning timber
        of cedar, and concerning timber of fir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My servants shall bring <i>them</i> down from Lebanon unto the sea:
        and I will convey them by sea in floats unto the place that thou shalt appoint
        me, and will cause them to be discharged there, and thou shalt receive <i>them:</i>
        and thou shalt accomplish my desire, in giving food for my household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Hiram gave Solomon cedar trees and fir trees <i>according to</i>
        all his desire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Solomon gave Hiram twenty thousand measures of wheat <i>for</i>
        food to his household, and twenty measures of pure oil: thus gave Solomon
        to Hiram year by year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> gave Solomon wisdom, as he promised
        him: and there was peace between Hiram and Solomon; and they two made a league
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And king Solomon raised a levy out of all Israel; and the levy was
        thirty thousand men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he sent them to Lebanon, ten thousand a month by courses: a month
        they were in Lebanon, <i>and</i> two months at home: and Adoniram <i>was</i>
        over the levy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Solomon had threescore and ten thousand that bare burdens, and
        fourscore thousand hewers in the mountains; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'beside the chief of Solomon''s officers which <i>were</i> over the
        work, three thousand and three hundred, which ruled over the people that
        wrought in the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the king commanded, and they brought great stones, costly stones,
        <i>and</i> hewed stones, to lay the foundation of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Solomon''s builders and Hiram''s builders did hew <i>them</i>,
        and the stonesquarers: so they prepared timber and stones to build the house.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The House of the Lord'
      title: The House of the Lord
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass in the four hundred and eightieth year after
        the children of Israel were come out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth
        year of Solomon''s reign over Israel, in the month Zif, which <i>is</i> the
        second month, that he began to build the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the house which king Solomon built for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        the length thereof <i>was</i> threescore cubits, and the breadth thereof
        twenty <i>cubits</i>, and the height thereof thirty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the porch before the temple of the house, twenty cubits <i>was</i>
        the length thereof, according to the breadth of the house; <i>and</i> ten
        cubits <i>was</i> the breadth thereof before the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And for the house he made windows of narrow lights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And against the wall of the house he built chambers round about,
        <i>against</i> the walls of the house round about, <i>both</i> of the temple
        and of the oracle: and he made chambers round about: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'the nethermost chamber <i>was</i> five cubits broad, and the middle
        <i>was</i> six cubits broad, and the third <i>was</i> seven cubits broad:
        for without <i>in the wall</i> of the house he made narrowed rests round
        about, that <i>the beams</i> should not be fastened in the walls of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the house, when it was in building, was built of stone made ready
        before it was brought thither: so that there was neither hammer nor axe <i>nor</i>
        any tool of iron heard in the house, while it was in building. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The door for the middle chamber <i>was</i> in the right side of the
        house: and they went up with winding stairs into the middle <i>chamber</i>,
        and out of the middle into the third. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So he built the house, and finished it; and covered the house with
        beams and boards of cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And <i>then</i> he built chambers against all the house, five cubits
        high: and they rested on the house with timber of cedar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Solomon,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<i>Concerning</i> this house which thou art in building, if thou
        wilt walk in my statutes, and execute my judgments, and keep all my commandments
        to walk in them; then will I perform my word with thee, which I spake unto
        David thy father: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and I will dwell among the children of Israel, and will not forsake
        my people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Solomon built the house, and finished it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he built the walls of the house within with boards of cedar,
        both the floor of the house, and the walls of the cieling: <i>and</i> he
        covered <i>them</i> on the inside with wood, and covered the floor of the
        house with planks of fir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he built twenty cubits on the sides of the house, both the floor
        and the walls with boards of cedar: he even built <i>them</i> for it within,
        <i>even</i> for the oracle, <i>even</i> for the most holy <i>place</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the house, that <i>is</i>, the temple before it, was forty cubits
        <i>long</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the cedar of the house within <i>was</i> carved with knops and
        open flowers: all <i>was</i> cedar; there was no stone seen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the oracle he prepared in the house within, to set there the
        ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the oracle in the forepart <i>was</i> twenty cubits in length,
        and twenty cubits in breadth, and twenty cubits in the height thereof: and
        he overlaid it with pure gold; and <i>so</i> covered the altar <i>which was
        of</i> cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Solomon overlaid the house within with pure gold: and he made
        a partition by the chains of gold before the oracle; and he overlaid it with
        gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the whole house he overlaid with gold, until he had finished
        all the house: also the whole altar that <i>was</i> by the oracle he overlaid
        with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And within the oracle he made two cherubims <i>of</i> olive tree,
        <i>each</i> ten cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And five cubits <i>was</i> the one wing of the cherub, and five cubits
        the other wing of the cherub: from the uttermost part of the one wing unto
        the uttermost part of the other <i>were</i> ten cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the other cherub <i>was</i> ten cubits: both the cherubims <i>were</i>
        of one measure and one size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The height of the one cherub <i>was</i> ten cubits, and so <i>was
        it</i> of the other cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And he set the cherubims within the inner house: and they stretched
        forth the wings of the cherubims, so that the wing of the one touched the
        <i>one</i> wall, and the wing of the other cherub touched the other wall;
        and their wings touched one another in the midst of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he overlaid the cherubims with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And he carved all the walls of the house round about with carved
        figures of cherubims and palm trees and open flowers, within and without. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the floor of the house he overlaid with gold, within and without. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And for the entering of the oracle he made doors <i>of</i> olive
        tree: the lintel <i>and</i> side posts <i>were</i> a fifth part <i>of the
        wall</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The two doors also <i>were of</i> olive tree; and he carved upon
        them carvings of cherubims and palm trees and open flowers, and overlaid
        <i>them</i> with gold, and spread gold upon the cherubims, and upon the palm
        trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So also made he for the door of the temple posts <i>of</i> olive
        tree, a fourth part <i>of the wall</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And the two doors <i>were of</i> fir tree: the two leaves of the
        one door <i>were</i> folding, and the two leaves of the other door <i>were</i>
        folding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And he carved <i>thereon</i> cherubims and palm trees and open flowers:
        and covered <i>them</i> with gold fitted upon the carved work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And he built the inner court with three rows of hewed stone, and
        a row of cedar beams.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'In the fourth year was the foundation of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        laid, in the month Zif: '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: and in the eleventh year, in the month Bul, which <i>is</i> the eighth
        month, was the house finished throughout all the parts thereof, and according
        to all the fashion of it. So was he seven years in building it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon''s House'
      title: Solomon's House
      number: 1
      content: '  But Solomon was building his own house thirteen years, and he finished
        all his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He built also the house of the forest of Lebanon; the length thereof
        <i>was</i> an hundred cubits, and the breadth thereof fifty cubits, and the
        height thereof thirty cubits, upon four rows of cedar pillars, with cedar
        beams upon the pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And <i>it was</i> covered with cedar above upon the beams, that <i>lay</i>
        on forty five pillars, fifteen <i>in</i> a row. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And <i>there were</i> windows <i>in</i> three rows, and light <i>was</i>
        against light <i>in</i> three ranks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And all the doors and posts <i>were</i> square, with the windows:
        and light <i>was</i> against light <i>in</i> three ranks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he made a porch of pillars; the length thereof <i>was</i> fifty
        cubits, and the breadth thereof thirty cubits: and the porch <i>was</i> before
        them: and the <i>other</i> pillars and the thick beam <i>were</i> before
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he made a porch for the throne where he might judge, <i>even</i>
        the porch of judgment: and <i>it was</i> covered with cedar from one side
        of the floor to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And his house where he dwelt <i>had</i> another court within the
        porch, <i>which</i> was of the like work. Solomon made also an house for
        Pharaoh''s daughter, whom he had taken <i>to wife</i>, like unto this porch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All these <i>were of</i> costly stones, according to the measures
        of hewed stones, sawed with saws, within and without, even from the foundation
        unto the coping, and <i>so</i> on the outside toward the great court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the foundation <i>was of</i> costly stones, <i>even</i> great
        stones, stones of ten cubits, and stones of eight cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And above <i>were</i> costly stones, after the measures of hewed
        stones, and cedars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Temple Furniture'
      title: Temple Furniture
      number: 12
      content: 'And the great court round about <i>was</i> with three rows of hewed
        stones, and a row of cedar beams, both for the inner court of the house of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and for the porch of the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And king Solomon sent and fetched Hiram out of Tyre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He <i>was</i> a widow''s son of the tribe of Naphtali, and his father
        <i>was</i> a man of Tyre, a worker in brass: and he was filled with wisdom,
        and understanding, and cunning to work all works in brass. And he came to
        king Solomon, and wrought all his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For he cast two pillars of brass, of eighteen cubits high apiece:
        and a line of twelve cubits did compass either of them about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he made two chapiters <i>of</i> molten brass, to set upon the
        tops of the pillars: the height of the one chapiter <i>was</i> five cubits,
        and the height of the other chapiter <i>was</i> five cubits: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<i>and</i> nets of checker work, and wreaths of chain work, for the
        chapiters which <i>were</i> upon the top of the pillars; seven for the one
        chapiter, and seven for the other chapiter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he made the pillars, and two rows round about upon the one network,
        to cover the chapiters that <i>were</i> upon the top, with pomegranates:
        and so did he for the other chapiter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the chapiters that <i>were</i> upon the top of the pillars <i>were</i>
        of lily work in the porch, four cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the chapiters upon the two pillars <i>had pomegranates</i> also
        above, over against the belly which <i>was</i> by the network: and the pomegranates
        <i>were</i> two hundred in rows round about upon the other chapiter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And he set up the pillars in the porch of the temple: and he set
        up the right pillar, and called the name thereof Jachin: and he set up the
        left pillar, and called the name thereof Boaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And upon the top of the pillars <i>was</i> lily work: so was the
        work of the pillars finished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he made a molten sea, ten cubits from the one brim to the other:
        <i>it was</i> round all about, and his height <i>was</i> five cubits: and
        a line of thirty cubits did compass it round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And under the brim of it round about <i>there were</i> knops compassing
        it, ten in a cubit, compassing the sea round about: the knops <i>were</i>
        cast in two rows, when it was cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It stood upon twelve oxen, three looking toward the north, and three
        looking toward the west, and three looking toward the south, and three looking
        toward the east: and the sea <i>was set</i> above upon them, and all their
        hinder parts <i>were</i> inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And it <i>was</i> an hand breadth thick, and the brim thereof was
        wrought like the brim of a cup, with flowers of lilies: it contained two
        thousand baths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And he made ten bases of brass; four cubits <i>was</i> the length
        of one base, and four cubits the breadth thereof, and three cubits the height
        of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the work of the bases <i>was</i> on this <i>manner:</i> they
        had borders, and the borders <i>were</i> between the ledges: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and on the borders that <i>were</i> between the ledges <i>were</i>
        lions, oxen, and cherubims: and upon the ledges <i>there was</i> a base above:
        and beneath the lions and oxen <i>were</i> certain additions made of thin
        work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And every base had four brasen wheels, and plates of brass: and the
        four corners thereof had undersetters: under the laver <i>were</i> undersetters
        molten, at the side of every addition. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the mouth of it within the chapiter and above <i>was</i> a cubit:
        but the mouth thereof <i>was</i> round <i>after</i> the work of the base,
        a cubit and an half: and also upon the mouth of it <i>were</i> gravings with
        their borders, foursquare, not round. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And under the borders <i>were</i> four wheels; and the axletrees
        of the wheels <i>were joined</i> to the base: and the height of a wheel <i>was</i>
        a cubit and half a cubit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the work of the wheels <i>was</i> like the work of a chariot
        wheel: their axletrees, and their naves, and their felloes, and their spokes,
        <i>were</i> all molten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And <i>there were</i> four undersetters to the four corners of one
        base: <i>and</i> the undersetters <i>were</i> of the very base itself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And in the top of the base <i>was there</i> a round compass of half
        a cubit high: and on the top of the base the ledges thereof and the borders
        thereof <i>were</i> of the same. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For on the plates of the ledges thereof, and on the borders thereof,
        he graved cherubims, lions, and palm trees, according to the proportion of
        every one, and additions round about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'After this <i>manner</i> he made the ten bases: all of them had one
        casting, one measure, <i>and</i> one size.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then made he ten lavers of brass: one laver contained forty baths:
        <i>and</i> every laver was four cubits: <i>and</i> upon every one of the
        ten bases one laver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And he put five bases on the right side of the house, and five on
        the left side of the house: and he set the sea on the right side of the house
        eastward over against the south.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And Hiram made the lavers, and the shovels, and the basons. So Hiram
        made an end of doing all the work that he made king Solomon for the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the two pillars, and the <i>two</i> bowls of the chapiters that <i>were</i>
        on the top of the two pillars; and the two networks, to cover the two bowls
        of the chapiters which <i>were</i> upon the top of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and four hundred pomegranates for the two networks, <i>even</i> two
        rows of pomegranates for one network, to cover the two bowls of the chapiters
        that <i>were</i> upon the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'and the ten bases, and ten lavers on the bases; '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'and one sea, and twelve oxen under the sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'and the pots, and the shovels, and the basons: and all these vessels,
        which Hiram made to king Solomon for the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        <i>were of</i> bright brass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'In the plain of Jordan did the king cast them, in the clay ground
        between Succoth and Zarthan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And Solomon left all the vessels <i>unweighed</i>, because they were
        exceeding many: neither was the weight of the brass found out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And Solomon made all the vessels that <i>pertained</i> unto the house
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: the altar of gold, and the table of gold,
        whereupon the shewbread <i>was</i>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'and the candlesticks of pure gold, five on the right <i>side</i>,
        and five on the left, before the oracle, with the flowers, and the lamps,
        and the tongs <i>of</i> gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: The Dedication'
      title: The Dedication
      number: 50
      content: 'and the bowls, and the snuffers, and the basons, and the spoons,
        and the censers <i>of</i> pure gold; and the hinges <i>of</i> gold, <i>both</i>
        for the doors of the inner house, the most holy <i>place, and</i> for the
        doors of the house, <i>to wit</i>, of the temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: So was ended all the work that king Solomon made for the house of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. And Solomon brought in the things which
        David his father had dedicated; <i>even</i> the silver, and the gold, and
        the vessels, did he put among the treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel, and all the heads
        of the tribes, the chief of the fathers of the children of Israel, unto king
        Solomon in Jerusalem, that they might bring up the ark of the covenant of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> out of the city of David, which <i>is</i>
        Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And all the men of Israel assembled themselves unto king Solomon
        at the feast in the month Ethanim, which <i>is</i> the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And all the elders of Israel came, and the priests took up the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they brought up the ark of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and
        the tabernacle of the congregation, and all the holy vessels that <i>were</i>
        in the tabernacle, even those did the priests and the Levites bring up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And king Solomon, and all the congregation of Israel, that were assembled
        unto him, <i>were</i> with him before the ark, sacrificing sheep and oxen,
        that could not be told nor numbered for multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the priests brought in the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        unto his place, into the oracle of the house, to the most holy <i>place,
        even</i> under the wings of the cherubims. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the cherubims spread forth <i>their</i> two wings over the place
        of the ark, and the cherubims covered the ark and the staves thereof above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they drew out the staves, that the ends of the staves were seen
        out in the holy <i>place</i> before the oracle, and they were not seen without:
        and there they are unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<i>There was</i> nothing in the ark save the two tables of stone,
        which Moses put there at Horeb, when the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> made
        <i>a covenant</i> with the children of Israel, when they came out of the
        land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the priests were come out of the holy <i>place</i>,
        that the cloud filled the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud:
        for the glory of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had filled the house of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then spake Solomon, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said that he
        would dwell in the thick darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I have surely built thee an house to dwell in, a settled place for
        thee to abide in for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the king turned his face about, and blessed all the congregation
        of Israel: (and all the congregation of Israel stood;) '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and he said, Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel, which spake with his mouth unto David my father, and hath with
        his hand fulfilled <i>it</i>, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Since the day that I brought forth my people Israel out of Egypt,
        I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel to build an house, that my
        name might be therein; but I chose David to be over my people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it was in the heart of David my father to build an house for
        the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto David my father, Whereas
        it was in thine heart to build an house unto my name, thou didst well that
        it was in thine heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Nevertheless thou shalt not build the house; but thy son that shall
        come forth out of thy loins, he shall build the house unto my name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath performed his word that
        he spake, and I am risen up in the room of David my father, and sit on the
        throne of Israel, as the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> promised, and have built
        an house for the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Solomon''s Prayer'
      title: Solomon's Prayer
      number: 21
      content: 'And I have set there a place for the ark, wherein <i>is</i> the covenant
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which he made with our fathers, when
        he brought them out of the land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Solomon stood before the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        in the presence of all the congregation of Israel, and spread forth his hands
        toward heaven: '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and he said, <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, <i>there
        is</i> no God like thee, in heaven above, or on earth beneath, who keepest
        covenant and mercy with thy servants that walk before thee with all their
        heart: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'who hast kept with thy servant David my father that thou promisedst
        him: thou spakest also with thy mouth, and hast fulfilled <i>it</i> with
        thine hand, as <i>it is</i> this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore now, <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, keep with
        thy servant David my father that thou promisedst him, saying, There shall
        not fail thee a man in my sight to sit on the throne of Israel; so that thy
        children take heed to their way, that they walk before me as thou hast walked
        before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And now, O God of Israel, let thy word, I pray thee, be verified,
        which thou spakest unto thy servant David my father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But will God indeed dwell on the earth? behold, the heaven and heaven
        of heavens cannot contain thee; how much less this house that I have builded? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Yet have thou respect unto the prayer of thy servant, and to his
        supplication, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> my God, to hearken unto the cry
        and to the prayer, which thy servant prayeth before thee to day: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'that thine eyes may be open toward this house night and day, <i>even</i>
        toward the place of which thou hast said, My name shall be there: that thou
        mayest hearken unto the prayer which thy servant shall make toward this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And hearken thou to the supplication of thy servant, and of thy people
        Israel, when they shall pray toward this place: and hear thou in heaven thy
        dwelling place: and when thou hearest, forgive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'If any man trespass against his neighbour, and an oath be laid upon
        him to cause him to swear, and the oath come before thine altar in this house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'then hear thou in heaven, and do, and judge thy servants, condemning
        the wicked, to bring his way upon his head; and justifying the righteous,
        to give him according to his righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When thy people Israel be smitten down before the enemy, because
        they have sinned against thee, and shall turn again to thee, and confess
        thy name, and pray, and make supplication unto thee in this house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'then hear thou in heaven, and forgive the sin of thy people Israel,
        and bring them again unto the land which thou gavest unto their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When heaven is shut up, and there is no rain, because they have sinned
        against thee; if they pray toward this place, and confess thy name, and turn
        from their sin, when thou afflictest them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'then hear thou in heaven, and forgive the sin of thy servants, and
        of thy people Israel, that thou teach them the good way wherein they should
        walk, and give rain upon thy land, which thou hast given to thy people for
        an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'If there be in the land famine, if there be pestilence, blasting,
        mildew, locust, <i>or</i> if there be caterpiller; if their enemy besiege
        them in the land of their cities; whatsoever plague, whatsoever sickness
        <i>there be</i>; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'what prayer and supplication soever be <i>made</i> by any man, <i>or</i>
        by all thy people Israel, which shall know every man the plague of his own
        heart, and spread forth his hands toward this house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then hear thou in heaven thy dwelling place, and forgive, and do,
        and give to every man according to his ways, whose heart thou knowest; (for
        thou, <i>even</i> thou only, knowest the hearts of all the children of men;) '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'that they may fear thee all the days that they live in the land which
        thou gavest unto our fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Moreover concerning a stranger, that <i>is</i> not of thy people
        Israel, but cometh out of a far country for thy name''s sake; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '(for they shall hear of thy great name, and of thy strong hand, and
        of thy stretched out arm;) when he shall come and pray toward this house; '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'hear thou in heaven thy dwelling place, and do according to all that
        the stranger calleth to thee for: that all people of the earth may know thy
        name, to fear thee, as <i>do</i> thy people Israel; and that they may know
        that this house, which I have builded, is called by thy name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'If thy people go out to battle against their enemy, whithersoever
        thou shalt send them, and shall pray unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        toward the city which thou hast chosen, and <i>toward</i> the house that
        I have built for thy name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'then hear thou in heaven their prayer and their supplication, and
        maintain their cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'If they sin against thee, (for <i>there is</i> no man that sinneth
        not,) and thou be angry with them, and deliver them to the enemy, so that
        they carry them away captives unto the land of the enemy, far or near; '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<i>yet</i> if they shall bethink themselves in the land whither they
        were carried captives, and repent, and make supplication unto thee in the
        land of them that carried them captives, saying, We have sinned, and have
        done perversely, we have committed wickedness; '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'and <i>so</i> return unto thee with all their heart, and with all
        their soul, in the land of their enemies, which led them away captive, and
        pray unto thee toward their land, which thou gavest unto their fathers, the
        city which thou hast chosen, and the house which I have built for thy name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'then hear thou their prayer and their supplication in heaven thy
        dwelling place, and maintain their cause, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'and forgive thy people that have sinned against thee, and all their
        transgressions wherein they have transgressed against thee, and give them
        compassion before them who carried them captive, that they may have compassion
        on them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'for they <i>be</i> thy people, and thine inheritance, which thou
        broughtest forth out of Egypt, from the midst of the furnace of iron: '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'that thine eyes may be open unto the supplication of thy servant,
        and unto the supplication of thy people Israel, to hearken unto them in all
        that they call for unto thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: His Blessing'
      title: His Blessing
      number: 53
      content: 'For thou didst separate them from among all the people of the earth,
        <i>to be</i> thine inheritance, as thou spakest by the hand of Moses thy
        servant, when thou broughtest our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord <smallcaps>GOD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'And it was <i>so</i>, that when Solomon had made an end of praying
        all this prayer and supplication unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, he
        arose from before the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, from kneeling
        on his knees with his hands spread up to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And he stood, and blessed all the congregation of Israel with a loud
        voice, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Blessed <i>be</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, that hath given
        rest unto his people Israel, according to all that he promised: there hath
        not failed one word of all his good promise, which he promised by the hand
        of Moses his servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God be with us, as he was with
        our fathers: let him not leave us, nor forsake us: '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'that he may incline our hearts unto him, to walk in all his ways,
        and to keep his commandments, and his statutes, and his judgments, which
        he commanded our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'And let these my words, wherewith I have made supplication before
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, be nigh unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        our God day and night, that he maintain the cause of his servant, and the
        cause of his people Israel at all times, as the matter shall require: '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'that all the people of the earth may know that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>is</i> God, <i>and that there is</i> none else. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Let your heart therefore be perfect with the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        our God, to walk in his statutes, and to keep his commandments, as at this
        day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'And the king, and all Israel with him, offered sacrifice before the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'And Solomon offered a sacrifice of peace offerings, which he offered
        unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, two and twenty thousand oxen, and an
        hundred and twenty thousand sheep. So the king and all the children of Israel
        dedicated the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'The same day did the king hallow the middle of the court that <i>was</i>
        before the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: for there he offered
        burnt offerings, and meat offerings, and the fat of the peace offerings:
        because the brasen altar that <i>was</i> before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>was</i> too little to receive the burnt offerings, and meat offerings,
        and the fat of the peace offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'And at that time Solomon held a feast, and all Israel with him, a
        great congregation, from the entering in of Hamath unto the river of Egypt,
        before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> our God, seven days and seven days,
        <i>even</i> fourteen days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'On the eighth day he sent the people away: and they blessed the king,
        and went unto their tents joyful and glad of heart for all the goodness that
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> had done for David his servant, and for Israel
        his people.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God''s Covenant'
      title: God's Covenant
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass, when Solomon had finished the building of
        the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the king''s house, and
        all Solomon''s desire which he was pleased to do, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> appeared to Solomon the second
        time, as he had appeared unto him at Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto him, I have heard thy
        prayer and thy supplication, that thou hast made before me: I have hallowed
        this house, which thou hast built, to put my name there for ever; and mine
        eyes and mine heart shall be there perpetually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And if thou wilt walk before me, as David thy father walked, in integrity
        of heart, and in uprightness, to do according to all that I have commanded
        thee, <i>and</i> wilt keep my statutes and my judgments: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then I will establish the throne of thy kingdom upon Israel for ever,
        as I promised to David thy father, saying, There shall not fail thee a man
        upon the throne of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<i>But</i> if ye shall at all turn from following me, ye or your
        children, and will not keep my commandments <i>and</i> my statutes which
        I have set before you, but go and serve other gods, and worship them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then will I cut off Israel out of the land which I have given them;
        and this house, which I have hallowed for my name, will I cast out of my
        sight; and Israel shall be a proverb and a byword among all people: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and at this house, <i>which</i> is high, every one that passeth by
        it shall be astonished, and shall hiss; and they shall say, Why hath the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> done thus unto this land, and to this house? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Cities and Ships'
      title: Cities and Ships
      number: 9
      content: 'And they shall answer, Because they forsook the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        their God, who brought forth their fathers out of the land of Egypt, and
        have taken hold upon other gods, and have worshipped them, and served them:
        therefore hath the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> brought upon them all this
        evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And it came to pass at the end of twenty years, when Solomon had
        built the two houses, the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the
        king''s house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '(<i>now</i> Hiram the king of Tyre had furnished Solomon with cedar
        trees and fir trees, and with gold, according to all his desire,) that then
        king Solomon gave Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Hiram came out from Tyre to see the cities which Solomon had
        given him; and they pleased him not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he said, What cities <i>are</i> these which thou hast given me,
        my brother? And he called them the land of Cabul unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Hiram sent to the king sixscore talents of gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And this <i>is</i> the reason of the levy which king Solomon raised;
        for to build the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and his own house,
        and Millo, and the wall of Jerusalem, and Hazor, and Megiddo, and Gezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<i>For</i> Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up, and taken Gezer, and
        burnt it with fire, and slain the Canaanites that dwelt in the city, and
        given it <i>for</i> a present unto his daughter, Solomon''s wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Solomon built Gezer, and Beth-horon the nether, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and Baalath, and Tadmor in the wilderness, in the land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and all the cities of store that Solomon had, and cities for his
        chariots, and cities for his horsemen, and that which Solomon desired to
        build in Jerusalem, and in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<i>And</i> all the people <i>that were</i> left of the Amorites,
        Hittites, Perizzites, Hivites, and Jebusites, which <i>were</i> not of the
        children of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'their children that were left after them in the land, whom the children
        of Israel also were not able utterly to destroy, upon those did Solomon levy
        a tribute of bondservice unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But of the children of Israel did Solomon make no bondmen: but they
        <i>were</i> men of war, and his servants, and his princes, and his captains,
        and rulers of his chariots, and his horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These <i>were</i> the chief of the officers that <i>were</i> over
        Solomon''s work, five hundred and fifty, which bare rule over the people
        that wrought in the work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Pharaoh''s daughter came up out of the city of David unto her
        house which <i>Solomon</i> had built for her: then did he build Millo.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And three times in a year did Solomon offer burnt offerings and peace
        offerings upon the altar which he built unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and he burnt incense upon the altar that <i>was</i> before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
        So he finished the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And king Solomon made a navy of ships in Ezion-geber, which <i>is</i>
        beside Eloth, on the shore of the Red sea, in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Hiram sent in the navy his servants, shipmen that had knowledge
        of the sea, with the servants of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And they came to Ophir, and fetched from thence gold, four hundred
        and twenty talents, and brought <i>it</i> to king Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Queen of Sheba'
      title: The Queen of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: '  And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning
        the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, she came to prove him with hard
        questions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And she came to Jerusalem with a very great train, with camels that
        bare spices, and very much gold, and precious stones: and when she was come
        to Solomon, she communed with him of all that was in her heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Solomon told her all her questions: there was not <i>any</i>
        thing hid from the king, which he told her not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen all Solomon''s wisdom, and the
        house that he had built, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the meat of his table, and the sitting of his servants, and the
        attendance of his ministers, and their apparel, and his cupbearers, and his
        ascent by which he went up unto the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        there was no more spirit in her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And she said to the king, It was a true report that I heard in mine
        own land of thy acts and of thy wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Howbeit I believed not the words, until I came, and mine eyes had
        seen <i>it:</i> and, behold, the half was not told me: thy wisdom and prosperity
        exceedeth the fame which I heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Happy <i>are</i> thy men, happy <i>are</i> these thy servants, which
        stand continually before thee, <i>and</i> that hear thy wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Blessed be the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God, which delighted
        in thee, to set thee on the throne of Israel: because the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        loved Israel for ever, therefore made he thee king, to do judgment and justice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And she gave the king an hundred and twenty talents of gold, and
        of spices very great store, and precious stones: there came no more such
        abundance of spices as these which the queen of Sheba gave to king Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the navy also of Hiram, that brought gold from Ophir, brought
        in from Ophir great plenty of almug trees, and precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the king made of the almug trees pillars for the house of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and for the king''s house, harps also and psalteries
        for singers: there came no such almug trees, nor were seen unto this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Wealth and Splendour'
      title: Wealth and Splendour
      number: 13
      content: 'And king Solomon gave unto the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatsoever
        she asked, beside <i>that</i> which Solomon gave her of his royal bounty.
        So she turned and went to her own country, she and her servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was six hundred
        threescore and six talents of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'beside <i>that he had</i> of the merchantmen, and of the traffick
        of the spice merchants, and of all the kings of Arabia, and of the governors
        of the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And king Solomon made two hundred targets <i>of</i> beaten gold:
        six hundred <i>shekels</i> of gold went to one target. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And <i>he made</i> three hundred shields <i>of</i> beaten gold; three
        pound of gold went to one shield: and the king put them in the house of the
        forest of Lebanon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with
        the best gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The throne had six steps, and the top of the throne <i>was</i> round
        behind: and <i>there were</i> stays on either side on the place of the seat,
        and two lions stood beside the stays. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other upon
        the six steps: there was not the like made in any kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all king Solomon''s drinking vessels <i>were of</i> gold, and
        all the vessels of the house of the forest of Lebanon <i>were of</i> pure
        gold; none <i>were of</i> silver: it was nothing accounted of in the days
        of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the king had at sea a navy of Tharshish with the navy of Hiram:
        once in three years came the navy of Tharshish, bringing gold, and silver,
        ivory, and apes, and peacocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So king Solomon exceeded all the kings of the earth for riches and
        for wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And all the earth sought to Solomon, to hear his wisdom, which God
        had put in his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they brought every man his present, vessels of silver, and vessels
        of gold, and garments, and armour, and spices, horses, and mules, a rate
        year by year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Solomon gathered together chariots and horsemen: and he had a
        thousand and four hundred chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen, whom he
        bestowed in the cities for chariots, and with the king at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the king made silver <i>to be</i> in Jerusalem as stones, and
        cedars made he <i>to be</i> as the sycomore trees that <i>are</i> in the
        vale, for abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Solomon had horses brought out of Egypt, and linen yarn: the
        king''s merchants received the linen yarn at a price. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And a chariot came up and went out of Egypt for six hundred <i>shekels</i>
        of silver, and an horse for an hundred and fifty: and so for all the kings
        of the Hittites, and for the kings of Syria, did they bring <i>them</i> out
        by their means.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: His Fall'
      title: His Fall
      number: 1
      content: '  But king Solomon loved many strange women, together with the daughter
        of Pharaoh, women of the Moabites, Ammonites, Edomites, Zidonians, <i>and</i>
        Hittites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'of the nations <i>concerning</i> which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        said unto the children of Israel, Ye shall not go in to them, neither shall
        they come in unto you: <i>for</i> surely they will turn away your heart after
        their gods: Solomon clave unto these in love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he had seven hundred wives, princesses, and three hundred concubines:
        and his wives turned away his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For it came to pass, when Solomon was old, <i>that</i> his wives
        turned away his heart after other gods: and his heart was not perfect with
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his God, as <i>was</i> the heart of David
        his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For Solomon went after Ashtoreth the goddess of the Zidonians, and
        after Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Solomon did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and went not fully after the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, as <i>did</i> David
        his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then did Solomon build an high place for Chemosh, the abomination
        of Moab, in the hill that <i>is</i> before Jerusalem, and for Molech, the
        abomination of the children of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And likewise did he for all his strange wives, which burnt incense
        and sacrificed unto their gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was angry with Solomon, because
        his heart was turned from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel,
        which had appeared unto him twice, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go
        after other gods: but he kept not that which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wherefore the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto Solomon, Forasmuch
        as this is done of thee, and thou hast not kept my covenant and my statutes,
        which I have commanded thee, I will surely rend the kingdom from thee, and
        will give it to thy servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Notwithstanding in thy days I will not do it for David thy father''s
        sake: <i>but</i> I will rend it out of the hand of thy son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Howbeit I will not rend away all the kingdom; <i>but</i> will give
        one tribe to thy son for David my servant''s sake, and for Jerusalem''s sake
        which I have chosen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> stirred up an adversary unto
        Solomon, Hadad the Edomite: he <i>was</i> of the king''s seed in Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For it came to pass, when David was in Edom, and Joab the captain
        of the host was gone up to bury the slain, after he had smitten every male
        in Edom; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '(for six months did Joab remain there with all Israel, until he had
        cut off every male in Edom:) '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'that Hadad fled, he and certain Edomites of his father''s servants
        with him, to go into Egypt; Hadad <i>being</i> yet a little child. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they arose out of Midian, and came to Paran: and they took men
        with them out of Paran, and they came to Egypt, unto Pharaoh king of Egypt;
        which gave him an house, and appointed him victuals, and gave him land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Hadad found great favour in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he
        gave him to wife the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the sister of Tahpenes bare him Genubath his son, whom Tahpenes
        weaned in Pharaoh''s house: and Genubath was in Pharaoh''s household among
        the sons of Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Hadad heard in Egypt that David slept with his fathers,
        and that Joab the captain of the host was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, Let
        me depart, that I may go to mine own country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Pharaoh said unto him, But what hast thou lacked with me, that,
        behold, thou seekest to go to thine own country? And he answered, Nothing:
        howbeit let me go in any wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And God stirred him up <i>another</i> adversary, Rezon the son of
        Eliadah, which fled from his lord Hadadezer king of Zobah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and he gathered men unto him, and became captain over a band, when
        David slew them <i>of Zobah:</i> and they went to Damascus, and dwelt therein,
        and reigned in Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Jeroboam''s Revolt'
      title: Jeroboam's Revolt
      number: 25
      content: 'And he was an adversary to Israel all the days of Solomon, beside
        the mischief that Hadad <i>did:</i> and he abhorred Israel, and reigned over
        Syria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephrathite of Zereda, Solomon''s
        servant, whose mother''s name <i>was</i> Zeruah, a widow woman, even he lifted
        up <i>his</i> hand against the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And this <i>was</i> the cause that he lifted up <i>his</i> hand against
        the king: Solomon built Millo, <i>and</i> repaired the breaches of the city
        of David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the man Jeroboam <i>was</i> a mighty man of valour: and Solomon
        seeing the young man that he was industrious, he made him ruler over all
        the charge of the house of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And it came to pass at that time when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem,
        that the prophet Ahijah the Shilonite found him in the way; and he had clad
        himself with a new garment; and they two <i>were</i> alone in the field: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and Ahijah caught the new garment that <i>was</i> on him, and rent
        it <i>in</i> twelve pieces: '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and he said to Jeroboam, Take thee ten pieces: for thus saith the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, Behold, I will rend the kingdom
        out of the hand of Solomon, and will give ten tribes to thee: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '(but he shall have one tribe for my servant David''s sake, and for
        Jerusalem''s sake, the city which I have chosen out of all the tribes of
        Israel:) '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'because that they have forsaken me, and have worshipped Ashtoreth
        the goddess of the Zidonians, Chemosh the god of the Moabites, and Milcom
        the god of the children of Ammon, and have not walked in my ways, to do <i>that
        which is</i> right in mine eyes, and <i>to keep</i> my statutes and my judgments,
        as <i>did</i> David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Howbeit I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand: but I
        will make him prince all the days of his life for David my servant''s sake,
        whom I chose, because he kept my commandments and my statutes: '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'but I will take the kingdom out of his son''s hand, and will give
        it unto thee, <i>even</i> ten tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And unto his son will I give one tribe, that David my servant may
        have a light alway before me in Jerusalem, the city which I have chosen me
        to put my name there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And I will take thee, and thou shalt reign according to all that
        thy soul desireth, and shalt be king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And it shall be, if thou wilt hearken unto all that I command thee,
        and wilt walk in my ways, and do <i>that is</i> right in my sight, to keep
        my statutes and my commandments, as David my servant did; that I will be
        with thee, and build thee a sure house, as I built for David, and will give
        Israel unto thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And I will for this afflict the seed of David, but not for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Solomon sought therefore to kill Jeroboam. And Jeroboam arose, and
        fled into Egypt, unto Shishak king of Egypt, and was in Egypt until the death
        of Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the rest of the acts of Solomon, and all that he did, and his
        wisdom, <i>are</i> they not written in the book of the acts of Solomon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And the time that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel <i>was</i>
        forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And Solomon slept with his fathers, and was buried in the city of
        David his father: and Rehoboam his son reigned in his stead.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Kingdom Divided'
      title: The Kingdom Divided
      number: 1
      content: '  And Rehoboam went to Shechem: for all Israel were come to Shechem
        to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who was yet
        in Egypt, heard <i>of it</i>, (for he was fled from the presence of king
        Solomon, and Jeroboam dwelt in Egypt;) '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that they sent and called him. And Jeroboam and all the congregation
        of Israel came, and spake unto Rehoboam, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thy father made our yoke grievous: now therefore make thou the grievous
        service of thy father, and his heavy yoke which he put upon us, lighter,
        and we will serve thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he said unto them, Depart yet <i>for</i> three days, then come
        again to me. And the people departed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And king Rehoboam consulted with the old men, that stood before Solomon
        his father while he yet lived, and said, How do ye advise that I may answer
        this people? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they spake unto him, saying, If thou wilt be a servant unto this
        people this day, and wilt serve them, and answer them, and speak good words
        to them, then they will be thy servants for ever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But he forsook the counsel of the old men, which they had given him,
        and consulted with the young men that were grown up with him, <i>and</i>
        which stood before him: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and he said unto them, What counsel give ye that we may answer this
        people, who have spoken to me, saying, Make the yoke which thy father did
        put upon us lighter? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the young men that were grown up with him spake unto him, saying,
        Thus shalt thou speak unto this people that spake unto thee, saying, Thy
        father made our yoke heavy, but make thou <i>it</i> lighter unto us; thus
        shalt thou say unto them, My little <i>finger</i> shall be thicker than my
        father''s loins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And now whereas my father did lade you with a heavy yoke, I will
        add to your yoke: my father hath chastised you with whips, but I will chastise
        you with scorpions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as
        the king had appointed, saying, Come to me again the third day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the king answered the people roughly, and forsook the old men''s
        counsel that they gave him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and spake to them after the counsel of the young men, saying, My
        father made your yoke heavy, and I will add to your yoke: my father <i>also</i>
        chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scorpions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Wherefore the king hearkened not unto the people; for the cause was
        from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, that he might perform his saying, which
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> spake by Ahijah the Shilonite unto Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So when all Israel saw that the king hearkened not unto them, the
        people answered the king, saying, What portion have we in David? neither
        <i>have we</i> inheritance in the son of Jesse: to your tents, O Israel:
        now see to thine own house, David. So Israel departed unto their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But <i>as for</i> the children of Israel which dwelt in the cities
        of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then king Rehoboam sent Adoram, who <i>was</i> over the tribute;
        and all Israel stoned him with stones, that he died. Therefore king Rehoboam
        made speed to get him up to his chariot, to flee to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Israel rebelled against the house of David unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And it came to pass, when all Israel heard that Jeroboam was come
        again, that they sent and called him unto the congregation, and made him
        king over all Israel: there was none that followed the house of David, but
        the tribe of Judah only.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Rehoboam was come to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house
        of Judah, with the tribe of Benjamin, an hundred and fourscore thousand chosen
        men, which were warriors, to fight against the house of Israel, to bring
        the kingdom again to Rehoboam the son of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the word of God came unto Shemaiah the man of God, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Speak unto Rehoboam, the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and unto
        all the house of Judah and Benjamin, and to the remnant of the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Ye shall not go up, nor
        fight against your brethren the children of Israel: return every man to his
        house; for this thing is from me. They hearkened therefore to the word of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and returned to depart, according to the
        word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Golden Calves'
      title: Golden Calves
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem in mount Ephraim, and dwelt therein;
        and went out from thence, and built Penuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Jeroboam said in his heart, Now shall the kingdom return to the
        house of David: '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'if this people go up to do sacrifice in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        at Jerusalem, then shall the heart of this people turn again unto their lord,
        <i>even</i> unto Rehoboam king of Judah, and they shall kill me, and go again
        to Rehoboam king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Whereupon the king took counsel, and made two calves <i>of</i> gold,
        and said unto them, It is too much for you to go up to Jerusalem: behold
        thy gods, O Israel, which brought thee up out of the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And he set the one in Beth-el, and the other put he in Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And this thing became a sin: for the people went <i>to worship</i>
        before the one, <i>even</i> unto Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And he made an house of high places, and made priests of the lowest
        of the people, which were not of the sons of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Jeroboam ordained a feast in the eighth month, on the fifteenth
        day of the month, like unto the feast that <i>is</i> in Judah, and he offered
        upon the altar. So did he in Beth-el, sacrificing unto the calves that he
        had made: and he placed in Beth-el the priests of the high places which he
        had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So he offered upon the altar which he had made in Beth-el the fifteenth
        day of the eighth month, <i>even</i> in the month which he had devised of
        his own heart; and ordained a feast unto the children of Israel: and he offered
        upon the altar, and burnt incense.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: At Beth-el''s Altar'
      title: At Beth-el's Altar
      number: 1
      content: '  And, behold, there came a man of God out of Judah by the word of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> unto Beth-el: and Jeroboam stood by the altar
        to burn incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he cried against the altar in the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and said, O altar, altar, thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; Behold,
        a child shall be born unto the house of David, Josiah by name; and upon thee
        shall he offer the priests of the high places that burn incense upon thee,
        and men''s bones shall be burnt upon thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he gave a sign the same day, saying, This <i>is</i> the sign
        which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath spoken; Behold, the altar shall
        be rent, and the ashes that <i>are</i> upon it shall be poured out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it came to pass, when king Jeroboam heard the saying of the man
        of God, which had cried against the altar in Beth-el, that he put forth his
        hand from the altar, saying, Lay hold on him. And his hand, which he put
        forth against him, dried up, so that he could not pull it in again to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The altar also was rent, and the ashes poured out from the altar,
        according to the sign which the man of God had given by the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the king answered and said unto the man of God, Intreat now the
        face of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God, and pray for me, that my
        hand may be restored me again. And the man of God besought the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and the king''s hand was restored him again, and became as <i>it was</i>
        before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the king said unto the man of God, Come home with me, and refresh
        thyself, and I will give thee a reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the man of God said unto the king, If thou wilt give me half
        thine house, I will not go in with thee, neither will I eat bread nor drink
        water in this place: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'for so was it charged me by the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        saying, Eat no bread, nor drink water, nor turn again by the same way that
        thou camest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So he went another way, and returned not by the way that he came
        to Beth-el.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now there dwelt an old prophet in Beth-el; and his sons came and
        told him all the works that the man of God had done that day in Beth-el:
        the words which he had spoken unto the king, them they told also to their
        father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And their father said unto them, What way went he? For his sons had
        seen what way the man of God went, which came from Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he said unto his sons, Saddle me the ass. So they saddled him
        the ass: and he rode thereon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and went after the man of God, and found him sitting under an oak:
        and he said unto him, <i>Art</i> thou the man of God that camest from Judah?
        And he said, I <i>am</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then he said unto him, Come home with me, and eat bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he said, I may not return with thee, nor go in with thee: neither
        will I eat bread nor drink water with thee in this place: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for it was said to me by the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        Thou shalt eat no bread nor drink water there, nor turn again to go by the
        way that thou camest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He said unto him, I <i>am</i> a prophet also as thou <i>art</i>;
        and an angel spake unto me by the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        saying, Bring him back with thee into thine house, that he may eat bread
        and drink water. <i>But</i> he lied unto him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So he went back with him, and did eat bread in his house, and drank
        water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And it came to pass, as they sat at the table, that the word of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto the prophet that brought him back: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and he cried unto the man of God that came from Judah, saying, Thus
        saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Forasmuch as thou hast disobeyed the
        mouth of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and hast not kept the commandment
        which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God commanded thee, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'but camest back, and hast eaten bread and drunk water in the place,
        of the which <i>the </i><smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> did say to thee, Eat
        no bread, and drink no water; thy carcase shall not come unto the sepulchre
        of thy fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And it came to pass, after he had eaten bread, and after he had drunk,
        that he saddled for him the ass, <i>to wit</i>, for the prophet whom he had
        brought back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And when he was gone, a lion met him by the way, and slew him: and
        his carcase was cast in the way, and the ass stood by it, the lion also stood
        by the carcase. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And, behold, men passed by, and saw the carcase cast in the way,
        and the lion standing by the carcase: and they came and told <i>it</i> in
        the city where the old prophet dwelt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when the prophet that brought him back from the way heard <i>thereof</i>,
        he said, It <i>is</i> the man of God, who was disobedient unto the word of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: therefore the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath delivered him unto the lion, which hath torn him, and slain him, according
        to the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which he spake unto him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And he spake to his sons, saying, Saddle me the ass. And they saddled
        <i>him</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he went and found his carcase cast in the way, and the ass and
        the lion standing by the carcase: the lion had not eaten the carcase, nor
        torn the ass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the prophet took up the carcase of the man of God, and laid it
        upon the ass, and brought it back: and the old prophet came to the city,
        to mourn and to bury him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And he laid his carcase in his own grave; and they mourned over him,
        <i>saying</i>, Alas, my brother! '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And it came to pass, after he had buried him, that he spake to his
        sons, saying, When I am dead, then bury me in the sepulchre wherein the man
        of God <i>is</i> buried; lay my bones beside his bones: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'for the saying which he cried by the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        against the altar in Beth-el, and against all the houses of the high places
        which <i>are</i> in the cities of Samaria, shall surely come to pass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'After this thing Jeroboam returned not from his evil way, but made
        again of the lowest of the people priests of the high places: whosoever would,
        he consecrated him, and he became <i>one</i> of the priests of the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And this thing became sin unto the house of Jeroboam, even to cut
        <i>it</i> off, and to destroy <i>it</i> from off the face of the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeroboam''s Son'
      title: Jeroboam's Son
      number: 1
      content: '  At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam fell sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Jeroboam said to his wife, Arise, I pray thee, and disguise thyself,
        that thou be not known to be the wife of Jeroboam; and get thee to Shiloh:
        behold, there <i>is</i> Ahijah the prophet, which told me that <i>I should
        be</i> king over this people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And take with thee ten loaves, and cracknels, and a cruse of honey,
        and go to him: he shall tell thee what shall become of the child. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Jeroboam''s wife did so, and arose, and went to Shiloh, and came
        to the house of Ahijah. But Ahijah could not see; for his eyes were set by
        reason of his age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto Ahijah, Behold, the
        wife of Jeroboam cometh to ask a thing of thee for her son; for he <i>is</i>
        sick: thus and thus shalt thou say unto her: for it shall be, when she cometh
        in, that she shall feign herself <i>to be</i> another <i>woman</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And it was <i>so</i>, when Ahijah heard the sound of her feet, as
        she came in at the door, that he said, Come in, thou wife of Jeroboam; why
        feignest thou thyself <i>to be</i> another? for I <i>am</i> sent to thee
        <i>with</i> heavy <i>tidings</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Go, tell Jeroboam, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God
        of Israel, Forasmuch as I exalted thee from among the people, and made thee
        prince over my people Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and rent the kingdom away from the house of David, and gave it thee:
        and <i>yet</i> thou hast not been as my servant David, who kept my commandments,
        and who followed me with all his heart, to do <i>that</i> only <i>which was</i>
        right in mine eyes; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but hast done evil above all that were before thee: for thou hast
        gone and made thee other gods, and molten images, to provoke me to anger,
        and hast cast me behind thy back: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'therefore, behold, I will bring evil upon the house of Jeroboam,
        and will cut off from Jeroboam him that pisseth against the wall, <i>and</i>
        him that is shut up and left in Israel, and will take away the remnant of
        the house of Jeroboam, as a man taketh away dung, till it be all gone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Him that dieth of Jeroboam in the city shall the dogs eat; and him
        that dieth in the field shall the fowls of the air eat: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath spoken <i>it</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Arise thou therefore, get thee to thine own house: <i>and</i> when
        thy feet enter into the city, the child shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And all Israel shall mourn for him, and bury him: for he only of
        Jeroboam shall come to the grave, because in him there is found <i>some</i>
        good thing toward the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel in the house
        of Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Moreover the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall raise him up a king
        over Israel, who shall cut off the house of Jeroboam that day: but what?
        even now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall smite Israel, as a reed
        is shaken in the water, and he shall root up Israel out of this good land,
        which he gave to their fathers, and shall scatter them beyond the river,
        because they have made their groves, provoking the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he shall give Israel up because of the sins of Jeroboam, who
        did sin, and who made Israel to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Jeroboam''s wife arose, and departed, and came to Tirzah: <i>and</i>
        when she came to the threshold of the door, the child died; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and they buried him; and all Israel mourned for him, according to
        the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which he spake by the hand of
        his servant Ahijah the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, how he warred, and how he reigned,
        behold, they <i>are</i> written in the book of the chronicles of the kings
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: JudahRehoboam'
      title: JudahRehoboam
      number: 20
      content: 'And the days which Jeroboam reigned <i>were</i> two and twenty years:
        and he slept with his fathers, and Nadab his son reigned in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. Rehoboam <i>was</i>
        forty and one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen
        years in Jerusalem, the city which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> did choose
        out of all the tribes of Israel, to put his name there. And his mother''s
        name <i>was</i> Naamah an Ammonitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Judah did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and they provoked him to jealousy with their sins which they had committed,
        above all that their fathers had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For they also built them high places, and images, and groves, on
        every high hill, and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And there were also sodomites in the land: <i>and</i> they did according
        to all the abominations of the nations which the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        cast out before the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And it came to pass in the fifth year of king Rehoboam, <i>that</i>
        Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and he took away the treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and the treasures of the king''s house; he even took away all: and he took
        away all the shields of gold which Solomon had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And king Rehoboam made in their stead brasen shields, and committed
        <i>them</i> unto the hands of the chief of the guard, which kept the door
        of the king''s house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And it was <i>so</i>, when the king went into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        that the guard bare them, and brought them back into the guard chamber.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam, and all that he did, <i>are</i>
        they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all <i>their</i>
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And Rehoboam slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers
        in the city of David. And his mother's name <i>was</i> Naamah an Ammonitess.
        And Abijam his son reigned in his stead.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abijam'
      title: Abijam
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in the eighteenth year of king Jeroboam the son of Nebat reigned
        Abijam over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Three years reigned he in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name <i>was</i>
        Maachah, the daughter of Abishalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he walked in all the sins of his father, which he had done before
        him: and his heart was not perfect with the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> his
        God, as the heart of David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Nevertheless for David''s sake did the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        his God give him a lamp in Jerusalem, to set up his son after him, and to
        establish Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'because David did <i>that which was</i> right in the eyes of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and turned not aside from any <i>thing</i> that
        he commanded him all the days of his life, save only in the matter of Uriah
        the Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Abijam, and all that he did, <i>are</i>
        they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? And
        there was war between Abijam and Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Asa'
      title: Asa
      number: 8
      content: 'And Abijam slept with his fathers; and they buried him in the city
        of David: and Asa his son reigned in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And in the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel reigned Asa
        over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And forty and one years reigned he in Jerusalem. And his mother''s
        name <i>was</i> Maachah, the daughter of Abishalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Asa did <i>that which was</i> right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        as <i>did</i> David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he took away the sodomites out of the land, and removed all the
        idols that his fathers had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And also Maachah his mother, even her he removed from <i>being</i>
        queen, because she had made an idol in a grove; and Asa destroyed her idol,
        and burnt <i>it</i> by the brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the high places were not removed: nevertheless Asa''s heart was
        perfect with the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> all his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he brought in the things which his father had dedicated, and
        the things which himself had dedicated, into the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        silver, and gold, and vessels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah, and built Ramah,
        that he might not suffer any to go out or come in to Asa king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Asa took all the silver and the gold <i>that were</i> left in
        the treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and the treasures
        of the king''s house, and delivered them into the hand of his servants: and
        king Asa sent them to Ben-hadad, the son of Tabrimon, the son of Hezion,
        king of Syria, that dwelt at Damascus, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<i>There is</i> a league between me and thee, <i>and</i> between
        my father and thy father: behold, I have sent unto thee a present of silver
        and gold; come and break thy league with Baasha king of Israel, that he may
        depart from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ben-hadad hearkened unto king Asa, and sent the captains of the
        hosts which he had against the cities of Israel, and smote Ijon, and Dan,
        and Abel-beth-maachah, and all Cinneroth, with all the land of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Baasha heard <i>thereof</i>, that he left
        off building of Ramah, and dwelt in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then king Asa made a proclamation throughout all Judah; none <i>was</i>
        exempted: and they took away the stones of Ramah, and the timber thereof,
        wherewith Baasha had builded; and king Asa built with them Geba of Benjamin,
        and Mizpah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The rest of all the acts of Asa, and all his might, and all that
        he did, and the cities which he built, <i>are</i> they not written in the
        book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? Nevertheless in the time of
        his old age he was diseased in his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: IsraelNadab'
      title: IsraelNadab
      number: 24
      content: 'And Asa slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in
        the city of David his father: and Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second
        year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned over Israel two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Baasha'
      title: Baasha
      number: 26
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin wherewith he made Israel
        to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house of Issachar, conspired
        against him; and Baasha smote him at Gibbethon, which <i>belonged</i> to
        the Philistines; for Nadab and all Israel laid siege to Gibbethon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Even in the third year of Asa king of Judah did Baasha slay him,
        and reigned in his stead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And it came to pass, when he reigned, <i>that</i> he smote all the
        house of Jeroboam; he left not to Jeroboam any that breathed, until he had
        destroyed him, according unto the saying of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        which he spake by his servant Ahijah the Shilonite: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'because of the sins of Jeroboam which he sinned, and which he made
        Israel sin, by his provocation wherewith he provoked the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel to anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Nadab, and all that he did, <i>are</i>
        they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their
        days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the third year of Asa king of Judah began Baasha the son of Ahijah
        to reign over all Israel in Tirzah, twenty and four years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And he did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and
        walked in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin wherewith he made Israel to
        sin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu'
      title: Jehu
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Jehu the
        son of Hanani against Baasha, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Forasmuch as I exalted thee out of the dust, and made thee prince
        over my people Israel; and thou hast walked in the way of Jeroboam, and hast
        made my people Israel to sin, to provoke me to anger with their sins; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'behold, I will take away the posterity of Baasha, and the posterity
        of his house; and will make thy house like the house of Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Him that dieth of Baasha in the city shall the dogs eat; and him
        that dieth of his in the fields shall the fowls of the air eat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Baasha, and what he did, and his might,
        <i>are</i> they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of
        Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Baasha slept with his fathers, and was buried in Tirzah: and Elah
        his son reigned in his stead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Civil War in Israel'
      title: Civil War in Israel
      number: 7
      content: 'And also by the hand of the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani came the
        word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> against Baasha, and against his house,
        even for all the evil that he did in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        in provoking him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house
        of Jeroboam; and because he killed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the twenty and sixth year of Asa king of Judah began Elah the
        son of Baasha to reign over Israel in Tirzah, two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And his servant Zimri, captain of half <i>his</i> chariots, conspired
        against him, as he was in Tirzah, drinking himself drunk in the house of
        Arza steward of <i>his</i> house in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Zimri went in and smote him, and killed him, in the twenty and
        seventh year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his stead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it came to pass, when he began to reign, as soon as he sat on
        his throne, <i>that</i> he slew all the house of Baasha: he left him not
        one that pisseth against a wall, neither of his kinsfolks, nor of his friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus did Zimri destroy all the house of Baasha, according to the
        word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which he spake against Baasha by
        Jehu the prophet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for all the sins of Baasha, and the sins of Elah his son, by which
        they sinned, and by which they made Israel to sin, in provoking the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel to anger with their vanities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Elah, and all that he did, <i>are</i>
        they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In the twenty and seventh year of Asa king of Judah did Zimri reign
        seven days in Tirzah. And the people <i>were</i> encamped against Gibbethon,
        which <i>belonged</i> to the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the people <i>that were</i> encamped heard say, Zimri hath conspired,
        and hath also slain the king: wherefore all Israel made Omri, the captain
        of the host, king over Israel that day in the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Omri went up from Gibbethon, and all Israel with him, and they
        besieged Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Zimri saw that the city was taken, that
        he went into the palace of the king''s house, and burnt the king''s house
        over him with fire, and died, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'for his sins which he sinned in doing evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        in walking in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin which he did, to make Israel
        to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Omri'
      title: Omri
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and his treason that he wrought,
        <i>are</i> they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of
        Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then were the people of Israel divided into two parts: half of the
        people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king; and half followed
        Omri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the people that followed Omri prevailed against the people that
        followed Tibni the son of Ginath: so Tibni died, and Omri reigned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the thirty and first year of Asa king of Judah began Omri to reign
        over Israel, twelve years: six years reigned he in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he bought the hill Samaria of Shemer for two talents of silver,
        and built on the hill, and called the name of the city which he built, after
        the name of Shemer, owner of the hill, Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But Omri wrought evil in the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and did worse than all that <i>were</i> before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For he walked in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and in
        his sin wherewith he made Israel to sin, to provoke the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel to anger with their vanities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Omri which he did, and his might that
        he shewed, <i>are</i> they not written in the book of the chronicles of the
        kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Ahab'
      title: Ahab
      number: 28
      content: 'So Omri slept with his fathers, and was buried in Samaria: and Ahab
        his son reigned in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And in the thirty and eighth year of Asa king of Judah began Ahab
        the son of Omri to reign over Israel: and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over
        Israel in Samaria twenty and two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        above all that <i>were</i> before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And it came to pass, as if it had been a light thing for him to walk
        in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, that he took to wife Jezebel the
        daughter of Ethbaal king of the Zidonians, and went and served Baal, and
        worshipped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he reared up an altar for Baal in the house of Baal, which he
        had built in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Ahab made a grove; and Ahab did more to provoke the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Israel to anger than all the kings of Israel that were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'In his days did Hiel the Beth-elite build Jericho: he laid the foundation
        thereof in Abiram his firstborn, and set up the gates thereof in his youngest
        <i>son</i> Segub, according to the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        which he spake by Joshua the son of Nun.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah'
      title: Elijah
      number: 1
      content: '  And Elijah the Tishbite, <i>who was</i> of the inhabitants of Gilead,
        said unto Ahab, <i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel liveth,
        before whom I stand, there shall not be dew nor rain these years, but according
        to my word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Get thee hence, and turn thee eastward, and hide thyself by the brook
        Cherith, that <i>is</i> before Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it shall be, <i>that</i> thou shalt drink of the brook; and I
        have commanded the ravens to feed thee there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So he went and did according unto the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        for he went and dwelt by the brook Cherith, that <i>is</i> before Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the ravens brought him bread and flesh in the morning, and bread
        and flesh in the evening; and he drank of the brook. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: At Zarephath'
      title: At Zarephath
      number: 7
      content: 'And it came to pass after a while, that the brook dried up, because
        there had been no rain in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came unto him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Arise, get thee to Zarephath, which <i>belongeth</i> to Zidon, and
        dwell there: behold, I have commanded a widow woman there to sustain thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So he arose and went to Zarephath. And when he came to the gate of
        the city, behold, the widow woman <i>was</i> there gathering of sticks: and
        he called to her, and said, Fetch me, I pray thee, a little water in a vessel,
        that I may drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And as she was going to fetch <i>it</i>, he called to her, and said,
        Bring me, I pray thee, a morsel of bread in thine hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And she said, <i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God liveth,
        I have not a cake, but an handful of meal in a barrel, and a little oil in
        a cruse: and, behold, I <i>am</i> gathering two sticks, that I may go in
        and dress it for me and my son, that we may eat it, and die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Elijah said unto her, Fear not; go <i>and</i> do as thou hast
        said: but make me thereof a little cake first, and bring <i>it</i> unto me,
        and after make for thee and for thy son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, The
        barrel of meal shall not waste, neither shall the cruse of oil fail, until
        the day <i>that</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> sendeth rain upon the
        earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And she went and did according to the saying of Elijah: and she,
        and he, and her house, did eat <i>many</i> days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<i>And</i> the barrel of meal wasted not, neither did the cruse of
        oil fail, according to the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, which
        he spake by Elijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it came to pass after these things, <i>that</i> the son of the
        woman, the mistress of the house, fell sick; and his sickness was so sore,
        that there was no breath left in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And she said unto Elijah, What have I to do with thee, O thou man
        of God? art thou come unto me to call my sin to remembrance, and to slay
        my son? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he said unto her, Give me thy son. And he took him out of her
        bosom, and carried him up into a loft, where he abode, and laid him upon
        his own bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he cried unto the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and said, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        my God, hast thou also brought evil upon the widow with whom I sojourn, by
        slaying her son? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And he stretched himself upon the child three times, and cried unto
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and said, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        my God, I pray thee, let this child''s soul come into him again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> heard the voice of Elijah; and
        the soul of the child came into him again, and he revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Elijah took the child, and brought him down out of the chamber
        into the house, and delivered him unto his mother: and Elijah said, See,
        thy son liveth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the woman said to Elijah, Now by this I know that thou <i>art</i>
        a man of God, <i>and</i> that the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        in thy mouth <i>is</i> truth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: In Samaria'
      title: In Samaria
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass <i>after</i> many days, that the word of the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Elijah in the third year, saying, Go,
        shew thyself unto Ahab; and I will send rain upon the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Elijah went to shew himself unto Ahab. And <i>there was</i> a
        sore famine in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Ahab called Obadiah, which <i>was</i> the governor of <i>his</i>
        house. (Now Obadiah feared the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> greatly: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for it was <i>so</i>, when Jezebel cut off the prophets of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        that Obadiah took an hundred prophets, and hid them by fifty in a cave, and
        fed them with bread and water.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Ahab said unto Obadiah, Go into the land, unto all fountains
        of water, and unto all brooks: peradventure we may find grass to save the
        horses and mules alive, that we lose not all the beasts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they divided the land between them to pass throughout it: Ahab
        went one way by himself, and Obadiah went another way by himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And as Obadiah was in the way, behold, Elijah met him: and he knew
        him, and fell on his face, and said, <i>Art</i> thou that my lord Elijah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he answered him, I <i>am:</i> go, tell thy lord, Behold, Elijah
        <i>is here</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he said, What have I sinned, that thou wouldest deliver thy servant
        into the hand of Ahab, to slay me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> thy God liveth, there is
        no nation or kingdom, whither my lord hath not sent to seek thee: and when
        they said, <i>He is</i> not <i>there</i>; he took an oath of the kingdom
        and nation, that they found thee not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And now thou sayest, Go, tell thy lord, Behold, Elijah <i>is here</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, <i>as soon as</i> I am gone from thee,
        that the Spirit of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall carry thee whither
        I know not; and <i>so</i> when I come and tell Ahab, and he cannot find thee,
        he shall slay me: but I thy servant fear the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        from my youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Was it not told my lord what I did when Jezebel slew the prophets
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, how I hid an hundred men of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>''s
        prophets by fifty in a cave, and fed them with bread and water? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And now thou sayest, Go, tell thy lord, Behold, Elijah <i>is here:</i>
        and he shall slay me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Elijah said, <i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> of hosts
        liveth, before whom I stand, I will surely shew myself unto him to day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and told him: and Ahab went to meet
        Elijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Ahab saw Elijah, that Ahab said unto him,
        <i>Art</i> thou he that troubleth Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he answered, I have not troubled Israel; but thou, and thy father''s
        house, in that ye have forsaken the commandments of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and thou hast followed Baalim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Mount Carmel'
      title: Mount Carmel
      number: 19
      content: 'Now therefore send, <i>and</i> gather to me all Israel unto mount
        Carmel, and the prophets of Baal four hundred and fifty, and the prophets
        of the groves four hundred, which eat at Jezebel''s table.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ahab sent unto all the children of Israel, and gathered the prophets
        together unto mount Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Elijah came unto all the people, and said, How long halt ye between
        two opinions? if the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>be</i> God, follow him:
        but if Baal, <i>then</i> follow him. And the people answered him not a word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then said Elijah unto the people, I, <i>even</i> I only, remain a
        prophet of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; but Baal''s prophets <i>are</i>
        four hundred and fifty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let them therefore give us two bullocks; and let them choose one
        bullock for themselves, and cut it in pieces, and lay <i>it</i> on wood,
        and put no fire <i>under:</i> and I will dress the other bullock, and lay
        <i>it</i> on wood, and put no fire <i>under:</i>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and call ye on the name of your gods, and I will call on the name
        of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>: and the God that answereth by fire, let
        him be God. And all the people answered and said, It is well spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Elijah said unto the prophets of Baal, Choose you one bullock
        for yourselves, and dress <i>it</i> first; for ye <i>are</i> many; and call
        on the name of your gods, but put no fire <i>under</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And they took the bullock which was given them, and they dressed
        <i>it</i>, and called on the name of Baal from morning even until noon, saying,
        O Baal, hear us. But <i>there was</i> no voice, nor any that answered. And
        they leaped upon the altar which was made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And it came to pass at noon, that Elijah mocked them, and said, Cry
        aloud: for he <i>is</i> a god; either he is talking, or he is pursuing, or
        he is in a journey, <i>or</i> peradventure he sleepeth, and must be awaked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they cried aloud, and cut themselves after their manner with
        knives and lancets, till the blood gushed out upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And it came to pass, when midday was past, and they prophesied until
        the <i>time</i> of the offering of the <i>evening</i> sacrifice, that <i>there
        was</i> neither voice, nor any to answer, nor any that regarded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Elijah said unto all the people, Come near unto me. And all the
        people came near unto him. And he repaired the altar of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>that was</i> broken down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Elijah took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes
        of the sons of Jacob, unto whom the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        came, saying, Israel shall be thy name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and with the stones he built an altar in the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        and he made a trench about the altar, as great as would contain two measures
        of seed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he put the wood in order, and cut the bullock in pieces, and
        laid <i>him</i> on the wood, and said, Fill four barrels with water, and
        pour <i>it</i> on the burnt sacrifice, and on the wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And he said, Do <i>it</i> the second time. And they did <i>it</i>
        the second time. And he said, Do <i>it</i> the third time. And they did <i>it</i>
        the third time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the water ran round about the altar; and he filled the trench
        also with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And it came to pass at <i>the time of</i> the offering of the <i>evening</i>
        sacrifice, that Elijah the prophet came near, and said, <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of Abraham, Isaac, and of Israel, let it be known this day that thou
        <i>art</i> God in Israel, and <i>that</i> I <i>am</i> thy servant, and <i>that</i>
        I have done all these things at thy word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Hear me, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, hear me, that this people
        may know that thou <i>art</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God, and <i>that</i>
        thou hast turned their heart back again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then the fire of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> fell, and consumed
        the burnt sacrifice, and the wood, and the stones, and the dust, and licked
        up the water that <i>was</i> in the trench. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And when all the people saw <i>it</i>, they fell on their faces:
        and they said, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, he <i>is</i> the God; the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, he <i>is</i> the God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And Elijah said unto them, Take the prophets of Baal; let not one
        of them escape. And they took them: and Elijah brought them down to the brook
        Kishon, and slew them there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Elijah said unto Ahab, Get thee up, eat and drink; for <i>there
        is</i> a sound of abundance of rain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So Ahab went up to eat and to drink. And Elijah went up to the top
        of Carmel; and he cast himself down upon the earth, and put his face between
        his knees, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'and said to his servant, Go up now, look toward the sea. And he went
        up, and looked, and said, <i>There is</i> nothing. And he said, Go again
        seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And it came to pass at the seventh time, that he said, Behold, there
        ariseth a little cloud out of the sea, like a man''s hand. And he said, Go
        up, say unto Ahab, Prepare <i>thy chariot</i>, and get thee down, that the
        rain stop thee not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And it came to pass in the mean while, that the heaven was black
        with clouds and wind, and there was a great rain. And Ahab rode, and went
        to Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: And the hand of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> was on Elijah; and
        he girded up his loins, and ran before Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: On Mount Horeb'
      title: On Mount Horeb
      number: 1
      content: '  And Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and withal how
        he had slain all the prophets with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Jezebel sent a messenger unto Elijah, saying, So let the gods
        do <i>to me</i>, and more also, if I make not thy life as the life of one
        of them by to morrow about this time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when he saw <i>that</i>, he arose, and went for his life, and
        came to Beer-sheba, which <i>belongeth</i> to Judah, and left his servant
        there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But he himself went a day''s journey into the wilderness, and came
        and sat down under a juniper tree: and he requested for himself that he might
        die; and said, It is enough; now, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, take away
        my life; for I <i>am</i> not better than my fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And as he lay and slept under a juniper tree, behold, then an angel
        touched him, and said unto him, Arise <i>and</i> eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he looked, and, behold, <i>there was</i> a cake baken on the
        coals, and a cruse of water at his head. And he did eat and drink, and laid
        him down again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the angel of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came again the second
        time, and touched him, and said, Arise <i>and</i> eat; because the journey
        <i>is</i> too great for thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he arose, and did eat and drink, and went in the strength of
        that meat forty days and forty nights unto Horeb the mount of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he came thither unto a cave, and lodged there; and, behold, the
        word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>came</i> to him, and he said
        unto him, What doest thou here, Elijah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he said, I have been very jealous for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of hosts: for the children of Israel have forsaken thy covenant, thrown
        down thine altars, and slain thy prophets with the sword; and I, <i>even</i>
        I only, am left; and they seek my life, to take it away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he said, Go forth, and stand upon the mount before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
        And, behold, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> passed by, and a great and strong
        wind rent the mountains, and brake in pieces the rocks before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>;
        <i>but</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>was</i> not in the wind: and
        after the wind an earthquake; <i>but</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>was</i> not in the earthquake: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and after the earthquake a fire; <i>but</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> 
        <i>was</i> not in the fire: and after the fire a still small voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it was <i>so</i>, when Elijah heard <i>it</i>, that he wrapped
        his face in his mantle, and went out, and stood in the entering in of the
        cave. And, behold, <i>there came</i> a voice unto him, and said, What doest
        thou here, Elijah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he said, I have been very jealous for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        God of hosts: because the children of Israel have forsaken thy covenant,
        thrown down thine altars, and slain thy prophets with the sword; and I, <i>even</i>
        I only, am left; and they seek my life, to take it away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto him, Go, return on
        thy way to the wilderness of Damascus: and when thou comest, anoint Hazael
        <i>to be</i> king over Syria: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Jehu the son of Nimshi shalt thou anoint <i>to be</i> king over
        Israel: and Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel-meholah shalt thou anoint <i>to
        be</i> prophet in thy room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, <i>that</i> him that escapeth the sword
        of Hazael shall Jehu slay: and him that escapeth from the sword of Jehu shall
        Elisha slay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Call of Elisha'
      title: The Call of Elisha
      number: 18
      content: 'Yet I have left <i>me</i> seven thousand in Israel, all the knees
        which have not bowed unto Baal, and every mouth which hath not kissed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So he departed thence, and found Elisha the son of Shaphat, who <i>was</i>
        plowing <i>with</i> twelve yoke <i>of oxen</i> before him, and he with the
        twelfth: and Elijah passed by him, and cast his mantle upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And he left the oxen, and ran after Elijah, and said, Let me, I pray
        thee, kiss my father and my mother, and <i>then</i> I will follow thee. And
        he said unto him, Go back again: for what have I done to thee? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And he returned back from him, and took a yoke of oxen, and slew them,
        and boiled their flesh with the instruments of the oxen, and gave unto the
        people, and they did eat. Then he arose, and went after Elijah, and ministered
        unto him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Syria Attacks Israel'
      title: Syria Attacks Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  And Ben-hadad the king of Syria gathered all his host together:
        and <i>there were</i> thirty and two kings with him, and horses, and chariots:
        and he went up and besieged Samaria, and warred against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he sent messengers to Ahab king of Israel into the city, and
        said unto him, Thus saith Ben-hadad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thy silver and thy gold <i>is</i> mine; thy wives also and thy children,
        <i>even</i> the goodliest, <i>are</i> mine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king of Israel answered and said, My lord, O king, according
        to thy saying, I <i>am</i> thine, and all that I have. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the messengers came again, and said, Thus speaketh Ben-hadad,
        saying, Although I have sent unto thee, saying, Thou shalt deliver me thy
        silver, and thy gold, and thy wives, and thy children; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'yet I will send my servants unto thee to morrow about this time,
        and they shall search thine house, and the houses of thy servants; and it
        shall be, <i>that</i> whatsoever is pleasant in thine eyes, they shall put
        <i>it</i> in their hand, and take <i>it</i> away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the king of Israel called all the elders of the land, and said,
        Mark, I pray you, and see how this <i>man</i> seeketh mischief: for he sent
        unto me for my wives, and for my children, and for my silver, and for my
        gold; and I denied him not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And all the elders and all the people said unto him, Hearken not
        <i>unto him</i>, nor consent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Wherefore he said unto the messengers of Ben-hadad, Tell my lord
        the king, All that thou didst send for to thy servant at the first I will
        do: but this thing I may not do. And the messengers departed, and brought
        him word again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Ben-hadad sent unto him, and said, The gods do so unto me, and
        more also, if the dust of Samaria shall suffice for handfuls for all the
        people that follow me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the king of Israel answered and said, Tell <i>him</i>, Let not
        him that girdeth on <i>his harness</i> boast himself as he that putteth it
        off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And it came to pass, when <i>Ben-hadad</i> heard this message, as
        he <i>was</i> drinking, he and the kings in the pavilions, that he said unto
        his servants, Set <i>yourselves in array</i>. And they set <i>themselves
        in array</i> against the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And, behold, there came a prophet unto Ahab king of Israel, saying,
        Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Hast thou seen all this great
        multitude? behold, I will deliver it into thine hand this day; and thou shalt
        know that I <i>am</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Ahab said, By whom? And he said, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        <i>Even</i> by the young men of the princes of the provinces. Then he said,
        Who shall order the battle? And he answered, Thou. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then he numbered the young men of the princes of the provinces, and
        they were two hundred and thirty two: and after them he numbered all the
        people, <i>even</i> all the children of Israel, <i>being</i> seven thousand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And they went out at noon. But Ben-hadad <i>was</i> drinking himself
        drunk in the pavilions, he and the kings, the thirty and two kings that helped
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the young men of the princes of the provinces went out first;
        and Ben-hadad sent out, and they told him, saying, There are men come out
        of Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he said, Whether they be come out for peace, take them alive;
        or whether they be come out for war, take them alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So these young men of the princes of the provinces came out of the
        city, and the army which followed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they slew every one his man: and the Syrians fled; and Israel
        pursued them: and Ben-hadad the king of Syria escaped on an horse with the
        horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the king of Israel went out, and smote the horses and chariots,
        and slew the Syrians with a great slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the prophet came to the king of Israel, and said unto him, Go,
        strengthen thyself, and mark, and see what thou doest: for at the return
        of the year the king of Syria will come up against thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the servants of the king of Syria said unto him, Their gods <i>are</i>
        gods of the hills; therefore they were stronger than we; but let us fight
        against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And do this thing, Take the kings away, every man out of his place,
        and put captains in their rooms: '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and number thee an army, like the army that thou hast lost, horse
        for horse, and chariot for chariot: and we will fight against them in the
        plain, <i>and</i> surely we shall be stronger than they. And he hearkened
        unto their voice, and did so.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And it came to pass at the return of the year, that Ben-hadad numbered
        the Syrians, and went up to Aphek, to fight against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the children of Israel were numbered, and were all present, and
        went against them: and the children of Israel pitched before them like two
        little flocks of kids; but the Syrians filled the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And there came a man of God, and spake unto the king of Israel, and
        said, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Because the Syrians have
        said, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> God of the hills, but he
        <i>is</i> not God of the valleys, therefore will I deliver all this great
        multitude into thine hand, and ye shall know that I <i>am</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And they pitched one over against the other seven days. And <i>so</i>
        it was, that in the seventh day the battle was joined: and the children of
        Israel slew of the Syrians an hundred thousand footmen in one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But the rest fled to Aphek, into the city; and <i>there</i> a wall
        fell upon twenty and seven thousand of the men <i>that were</i> left. And
        Ben-hadad fled, and came into the city, into an inner chamber.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And his servants said unto him, Behold now, we have heard that the
        kings of the house of Israel <i>are</i> merciful kings: let us, I pray thee,
        put sackcloth on our loins, and ropes upon our heads, and go out to the king
        of Israel: peradventure he will save thy life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So they girded sackcloth on their loins, and <i>put</i> ropes on
        their heads, and came to the king of Israel, and said, Thy servant Ben-hadad
        saith, I pray thee, let me live. And he said, <i>Is</i> he yet alive? he
        <i>is</i> my brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now the men did diligently observe whether <i>any thing would come</i>
        from him, and did hastily catch <i>it:</i> and they said, Thy brother Ben-hadad.
        Then he said, Go ye, bring him. Then Ben-hadad came forth to him; and he
        caused him to come up into the chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And <i>Ben-hadad</i> said unto him, The cities, which my father took
        from thy father, I will restore; and thou shalt make streets for thee in
        Damascus, as my father made in Samaria. Then <i>said Ahab</i>, I will send
        thee away with this covenant. So he made a covenant with him, and sent him
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And a certain man of the sons of the prophets said unto his neighbour
        in the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, Smite me, I pray thee. And
        the man refused to smite him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then said he unto him, Because thou hast not obeyed the voice of
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, behold, as soon as thou art departed from
        me, a lion shall slay thee. And as soon as he was departed from him, a lion
        found him, and slew him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then he found another man, and said, Smite me, I pray thee. And the
        man smote him, so that in smiting he wounded <i>him</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So the prophet departed, and waited for the king by the way, and
        disguised himself with ashes upon his face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And as the king passed by, he cried unto the king: and he said, Thy
        servant went out into the midst of the battle; and, behold, a man turned
        aside, and brought a man unto me, and said, Keep this man: if by any means
        he be missing, then shall thy life be for his life, or else thou shalt pay
        a talent of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And as thy servant was busy here and there, he was gone. And the
        king of Israel said unto him, So <i>shall</i> thy judgment <i>be</i>; thyself
        hast decided <i>it</i>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And he hasted, and took the ashes away from his face; and the king
        of Israel discerned him that he <i>was</i> of the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And he said unto him, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        Because thou hast let go out of <i>thy</i> hand a man whom I appointed to
        utter destruction, therefore thy life shall go for his life, and thy people
        for his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And the king of Israel went to his house heavy and displeased, and
        came to Samaria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Naboth''s Vineyard'
      title: Naboth's Vineyard
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came to pass after these things, <i>that</i> Naboth the
        Jezreelite had a vineyard, which <i>was</i> in Jezreel, hard by the palace
        of Ahab king of Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Ahab spake unto Naboth, saying, Give me thy vineyard, that I
        may have it for a garden of herbs, because it <i>is</i> near unto my house:
        and I will give thee for it a better vineyard than it; <i>or</i>, if it seem
        good to thee, I will give thee the worth of it in money. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Naboth said to Ahab, The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> forbid it
        me, that I should give the inheritance of my fathers unto thee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Ahab came into his house heavy and displeased because of the
        word which Naboth the Jezreelite had spoken to him: for he had said, I will
        not give thee the inheritance of my fathers. And he laid him down upon his
        bed, and turned away his face, and would eat no bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But Jezebel his wife came to him, and said unto him, Why is thy spirit
        so sad, that thou eatest no bread? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he said unto her, Because I spake unto Naboth the Jezreelite,
        and said unto him, Give me thy vineyard for money; or else, if it please
        thee, I will give thee <i>another</i> vineyard for it: and he answered, I
        will not give thee my vineyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Jezebel his wife said unto him, Dost thou now govern the kingdom
        of Israel? arise, <i>and</i> eat bread, and let thine heart be merry: I will
        give thee the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So she wrote letters in Ahab''s name, and sealed <i>them</i> with
        his seal, and sent the letters unto the elders and to the nobles that <i>were</i>
        in his city, dwelling with Naboth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And she wrote in the letters, saying, Proclaim a fast, and set Naboth
        on high among the people: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and set two men, sons of Belial, before him, to bear witness against
        him, saying, Thou didst blaspheme God and the king. And <i>then</i> carry
        him out, and stone him, that he may die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the men of his city, <i>even</i> the elders and the nobles who
        were the inhabitants in his city, did as Jezebel had sent unto them, <i>and</i>
        as it <i>was</i> written in the letters which she had sent unto them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They proclaimed a fast, and set Naboth on high among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And there came in two men, children of Belial, and sat before him:
        and the men of Belial witnessed against him, <i>even</i> against Naboth,
        in the presence of the people, saying, Naboth did blaspheme God and the king.
        Then they carried him forth out of the city, and stoned him with stones,
        that he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, Naboth is stoned, and is dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Jezebel heard that Naboth was stoned, and
        was dead, that Jezebel said to Ahab, Arise, take possession of the vineyard
        of Naboth the Jezreelite, which he refused to give thee for money: for Naboth
        is not alive, but dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Elijah denounces Ahab'
      title: Elijah denounces Ahab
      number: 16
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, that Ahab
        rose up to go down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession
        of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Elijah the
        Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, which <i>is</i> in Samaria:
        behold, <i>he is</i> in the vineyard of Naboth, whither he is gone down to
        possess it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And thou shalt speak unto him, saying, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        Hast thou killed, and also taken possession? And thou shalt speak unto him,
        saying, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, In the place where dogs
        licked the blood of Naboth shall dogs lick thy blood, even thine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Ahab said to Elijah, Hast thou found me, O mine enemy? And he
        answered, I have found <i>thee:</i> because thou hast sold thyself to work
        evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Behold, I will bring evil upon thee, and will take away thy posterity,
        and will cut off from Ahab him that pisseth against the wall, and him that
        is shut up and left in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and will make thine house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat,
        and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, for the provocation wherewith
        thou hast provoked <i>me</i> to anger, and made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And of Jezebel also spake the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, saying,
        The dogs shall eat Jezebel by the wall of Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Him that dieth of Ahab in the city the dogs shall eat; and him that
        dieth in the field shall the fowls of the air eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But there was none like unto Ahab, which did sell himself to work
        wickedness in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, whom Jezebel
        his wife stirred up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And he did very abominably in following idols, according to all <i>things</i>
        as did the Amorites, whom the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> cast out before
        the children of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And it came to pass, when Ahab heard those words, that he rent his
        clothes, and put sackcloth upon his flesh, and fasted, and lay in sackcloth,
        and went softly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> came to Elijah the
        Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Seest thou how Ahab humbleth himself before me? because he humbleth
        himself before me, I will not bring the evil in his days: <i>but</i> in his
        son''s days will I bring the evil upon his house.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Ahab'
      title: The Death of Ahab
      number: 1
      content: '  And they continued three years without war between Syria and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass in the third year, that Jehoshaphat the king
        of Judah came down to the king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the king of Israel said unto his servants, Know ye that Ramoth
        in Gilead <i>is</i> ours, and we <i>be</i> still, <i>and</i> take it not
        out of the hand of the king of Syria? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he said unto Jehoshaphat, Wilt thou go with me to battle to Ramoth-gilead?
        And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, I <i>am</i> as thou <i>art</i>,
        my people as thy people, my horses as thy horses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat said unto the king of Israel, Enquire, I pray thee,
        at the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> to day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four
        hundred men, and said unto them, Shall I go against Ramoth-gilead to battle,
        or shall I forbear? And they said, Go up; for the Lord shall deliver <i>it</i>
        into the hand of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat said, <i>Is there</i> not here a prophet of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        besides, that we might enquire of him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, <i>There is</i> yet
        one man, Micaiah the son of Imlah, by whom we may enquire of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        but I hate him; for he doth not prophesy good concerning me, but evil. And
        Jehoshaphat said, Let not the king say so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the king of Israel called an officer, and said, Hasten <i>hither</i>
        Micaiah the son of Imlah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah sat each
        on his throne, having put on their robes, in a void place in the entrance
        of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets prophesied before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made him horns of iron: and he
        said, Thus saith the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, With these shalt thou push
        the Syrians, until thou have consumed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, Go up to Ramoth-gilead,
        and prosper: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall deliver <i>it</i>
        into the king''s hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the messenger that was gone to call Micaiah spake unto him, saying,
        Behold now, the words of the prophets <i>declare</i> good unto the king with
        one mouth: let thy word, I pray thee, be like the word of one of them, and
        speak <i>that which is</i> good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Micaiah said, <i>As</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> liveth,
        what the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> saith unto me, that will I speak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So he came to the king. And the king said unto him, Micaiah, shall
        we go against Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall we forbear? And he answered
        him, Go, and prosper: for the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> shall deliver <i>it</i>
        into the hand of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the king said unto him, How many times shall I adjure thee that
        thou tell me nothing but <i>that which is</i> true in the name of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he said, I saw all Israel scattered upon the hills, as sheep
        that have not a shepherd: and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said, These
        have no master: let them return every man to his house in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, Did I not tell thee
        that he would prophesy no good concerning me, but evil? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he said, Hear thou therefore the word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        I saw the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> sitting on his throne, and all the
        host of heaven standing by him on his right hand and on his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said, Who shall persuade Ahab,
        that he may go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead? And one said on this manner,
        and another said on that manner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And there came forth a spirit, and stood before the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and said, I will persuade him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> said unto him, Wherewith? And
        he said, I will go forth, and I will be a lying spirit in the mouth of all
        his prophets. And he said, Thou shalt persuade <i>him</i>, and prevail also:
        go forth, and do so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now therefore, behold, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath put a
        lying spirit in the mouth of all these thy prophets, and the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath spoken evil concerning thee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah went near, and smote Micaiah on
        the cheek, and said, Which way went the Spirit of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        from me to speak unto thee? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Micaiah said, Behold, thou shalt see in that day, when thou shalt
        go into an inner chamber to hide thyself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the king of Israel said, Take Micaiah, and carry him back unto
        Amon the governor of the city, and to Joash the king''s son; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and say, Thus saith the king, Put this <i>fellow</i> in the prison,
        and feed him with bread of affliction and with water of affliction, until
        I come in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Micaiah said, If thou return at all in peace, the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath not spoken by me. And he said, Hearken, O people, every one of you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to
        Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, I will disguise myself,
        and enter into the battle; but put thou on thy robes. And the king of Israel
        disguised himself, and went into the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But the king of Syria commanded his thirty and two captains that
        had rule over his chariots, saying, Fight neither with small nor great, save
        only with the king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat,
        that they said, Surely it <i>is</i> the king of Israel. And they turned aside
        to fight against him: and Jehoshaphat cried out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And it came to pass, when the captains of the chariots perceived
        that it <i>was</i> not the king of Israel, that they turned back from pursuing
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And a <i>certain</i> man drew a bow at a venture, and smote the king
        of Israel between the joints of the harness: wherefore he said unto the driver
        of his chariot, Turn thine hand, and carry me out of the host; for I am wounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the battle increased that day: and the king was stayed up in
        his chariot against the Syrians, and died at even: and the blood ran out
        of the wound into the midst of the chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And there went a proclamation throughout the host about the going
        down of the sun, saying, Every man to his city, and every man to his own
        country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So the king died, and was brought to Samaria; and they buried the
        king in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And <i>one</i> washed the chariot in the pool of Samaria; and the
        dogs licked up his blood; and they washed his armour; according unto the
        word of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> which he spake. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahab, and all that he did, and the ivory
        house which he made, and all the cities that he built, <i>are</i> they not
        written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: The Two Kingdoms'
      title: The Two Kingdoms
      number: 40
      content: 'So Ahab slept with his fathers; and Ahaziah his son reigned in his
        stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat the son of Asa began to reign over Judah in the fourth
        year of Ahab king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Jehoshaphat <i>was</i> thirty and five years old when he began to
        reign; and he reigned twenty and five years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s
        name <i>was</i> Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And he walked in all the ways of Asa his father; he turned not aside
        from it, doing <i>that which was</i> right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:
        nevertheless the high places were not taken away; <i>for</i> the people offered
        and burnt incense yet in the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat made peace with the king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, and his might that he shewed,
        and how he warred, <i>are</i> they not written in the book of the chronicles
        of the kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And the remnant of the sodomites, which remained in the days of his
        father Asa, he took out of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<i>There was</i> then no king in Edom: a deputy <i>was</i> king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Jehoshaphat made ships of Tharshish to go to Ophir for gold: but
        they went not; for the ships were broken at Ezion-geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Then said Ahaziah the son of Ahab unto Jehoshaphat, Let my servants
        go with thy servants in the ships. But Jehoshaphat would not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers
        in the city of David his father: and Jehoram his son reigned in his stead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Ahaziah the son of Ahab began to reign over Israel in Samaria the
        seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and reigned two years over
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And he did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        and walked in the way of his father, and in the way of his mother, and in
        the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin: '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: for he served Baal, and worshipped him, and provoked to anger the
        <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> God of Israel, according to all that his father
        had done.
      comments: []
